title: steak and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Cut steak into thin strips and cook in oil until done.
Keep strips covered while cooking.
Dissolve beef cubes in boiling water.
Add beef water to cooked strips.
Add soy sauce and spices.
Add vegetables and cook until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: corned beef dip
directions: * Comes in a tin with a key.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces and place in large bowl. Steam chicken pieces with grated ginger.
Shred chicken and cool. Chop green onions.
Fry maifun (rice noodles) in hot oil and drain on paper towel until cool.
Place chicken, green onion and maifun over lettuce and refrigerate for half hour.
Add dressing and serve.

title: quick meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients and form meat loaf. Line a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with foil.
Press in beef mixture. Reduce heat to 400° and bake 45 minutes or until done.
Serve with parsley-potatoes and buttered broccoli.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour water over all-bran and raisins.
Cream oil and sugar; add eggs, hot bran and eggs with buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients.
Lastly, add bran flakes.
Mix to combine.
Bake in greased muffin pans at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: tuna burgers
directions: Mix it like you would tuna salad.
Put on hamburger buns; wrap in foil.
Put in oven; heat at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: batchelor's french fries
directions: Wash potatoes and cut (do not peel).
Put into cold water and let stand overnight in refrigerator until next day.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle potatoes with ginger and nutmeg, then dredge in flour.
Cook in hot oil.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Melt chocolate chips and wax in a double boiler.
Keep warm. Melt peanut butter and margarine.
Mix Rice Krispies and powdered sugar.
Pour peanut butter mixture over Rice Krispies and sugar mixture; mix well.
Form into 1-inch balls and dip into warm chocolate mix.
Cool on wax paper.

title: best ever cabbage soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer 2 hours. Refrigerate at least 24 hours before reheating to serve.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese thoroughly.
Beat cheese and Marshmallow Creme until well blended.
Great on all fruits except melons.

title: jiffy cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo into pan in which you are going to bake cobbler.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and milk. Make batter consistency of pancake batter.
Drain fruit.
Pour fruit over batter.
Pour juice (1 cup) over fruit.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Other fruits may be substituted.

title: herbed cornbread stuffing
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside. To skillet, add drippings, celery, onion and half of the broth; cover and simmer until barely tender, about 7 minutes.

title: snickerdoodle cookie
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients. Mix well. Shape into balls and roll in sugar and cinnamon. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400 degrees for 8-10 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Boil angel hair pasta until tender; drain and rinse with cold water.
Cut cucumber, tomatoes and onion into finely chopped pieces.
Sprinkle McCormick seasoning over the pasta.
Toss, add the vegetables and pour the salad dressing over the mixture.
Chill before serving.
Goes well with garlic toast.

title: reuben pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients except cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.
Top with cheese; bake 5 minutes longer.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: meat ball supreme
directions: Soften	bread
in
milk;
add egg.
Mix well with meat; add onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Form into balls; roll in flour. Brown
in
hot
shortening.
Add
Kitchen
Bouquet and tomato juice; simmer 10 minutes.
Add water, carrots and peas. Cover and simmer until hot through.
Serves 6.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil.
In a small pan, saute celery and onions in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add to stock.
Blanch bacon in a little hot water.
Add to stock and simmer.
When the mixture has come to a boil, add salt, pepper, thyme and potatoes. Simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: el paso casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Put noodles and ham in casserole dish. Mix butter, flour and milk in separate bowl. Add cheese to mixture, then pour over noodles and ham. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: In a large saucepan combine corn, potato, onion, water, bouillon granules and pepper.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 10 minutes or until corn and potatoes are just tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of the milk and the margarine or butter.
Combine the remaining milk and flour.
Stir the milk-flour mixture into the corn mixture.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Top with cheese.
Mix soup and milk or wine.
Spoon over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle margarine over all. Bake covered at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: homemade candy
directions: Mix well, then place in plate to cool.

title: sour cream tortillas (or pinwheels)
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill 1 hour, then spread mixture in tortilla shells and cut them into pinwheels.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut fruit and nuts fine.
Mix well with milk to coat fruit. Pack firmly in well-greased pans.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.

title: easy stew
directions: Cook in covered dish at 300° for 3 hours.
Add potatoes the last 45 minutes.

title: aunt mary ann's never fail pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar; cut in Crisco with a pastry blender.
Combine ice water, vinegar and egg; beat well.
Add liquids to flour mixture, 1 to 2 tablespoons at a time.
Knead slightly.
Form into 4 equal balls.
Freezes well if not all used at once.
Bake according to directions for pie filling being used.

title: sweet lovers fruit dip
directions: Make as much or as little as your heart desires.
Great with apples, fresh pineapple, strawberries, any fruit.

title: lumps
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream well the margarine/butter, powdered sugar and cornstarch.
Blend the flour into the creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
On ungreased cookie sheet, drop batter by teaspoonful or by "finger pinch."
Bake about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: soy marinade
directions: In a large, shallow dish, combine ingredients; add beef, pork or chicken.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Grill or broil as desired, basting frequently with additional ReaLemon juice concentrate. Refrigerate leftover meat.

title: five o'clock rolls
directions: Mix the yeast, sugar and warm water; let stand 15 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together; knead into a soft dough, barely holding its shape.
Punch down every hour until 10 o'clock (5 P.M. to 10 P.M.).
Shape and place on greased pans. Cover with cloth and plastic bag.
Bake early next morning at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: molded cranberry waldorf salad(heart healthy)
directions: Bring 1 cup cranberry juice to boil; stir in gelatin.
Add remaining juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apple and celery.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: velvet cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar and cream well.
Add unbeaten egg and extract.
Sift flour and baking powder and add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Use cookie press or drop on cookie sheet in small amounts. Do not grease or flour cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove from cookie sheet at once.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all the ingredients but the sherry in the top of a double boiler and heat until creamy.
Add sherry to taste (1/2 cup is not too much, depending on whether it is to be served from a chafing dish or as a dip where the texture should be slightly thicker).

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil together.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon together, then add to creamed sugar, eggs and oil.
Alternate with the small (3) jars of baby carrots.
Bake in large greased and floured cake pan (15 x 12-inch).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
When cold, put icing on cake.

title: reuben meat loaf
directions: Pinch up rye bread and pour milk over crumbs.
Add egg, hamburger and garlic salt to bread.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in loaf pan and cover with 1/2 can of sauerkraut and layer of Swiss cheese.
Repeat, except for cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 375° for an hour.
Remove foil.
Place remaining cheese on top and brown 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed shells
directions: Prick sausage with fork and parboil in small amount of water in covered skillet for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Chop sausage and fry along with onion.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add egg, bread and parsley and mix thoroughly.
Fill hot parboiled shells with sausage mixture.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, topping with spaghetti sauce.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle grated cheese and bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes more.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake 2 pie shells and let cool.
Mix flour, cocoa, sugar, eggs and milk.
Cook slowly in a thick pot, stirring constantly.
Cook for about 2 to 3 minutes after mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla flavoring.
Pour into pie shells.

title: pepper nuts
directions: Add flour to make really stiff dough.
Has to be stiff enough to stay together in long rolls, about 1/2-inch in diameter.
If not stiff enough to do that, add more flour.
After rolling, let set in refrigerator for a couple of hours.
Slice in little pieces on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until brown.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Spread all but 1 teaspoon butter on beef.
Place on a rack in a roasting pan.
Place, uncovered, in 400° oven for 20 minutes. While tenderloin is roasting, saute onion in remaining butter in small saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat and pour over meat.
Roast 20 to 25 minutes longer, basting often.
Serve remaining sauce with meat.
Grilled mushrooms may be added to the serving platter.
Serves 12.

title: doyle's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter. Pour into deep Pyrex or Corning Ware dish.
Mix next 3 ingredients into paste.
Spread as evenly as possible over melted butter.
Spread fruit evenly over this.
Pour a little of the fruit juice over it (reserve some juice).
Cook about 1 hour at 350° or until top is golden brown (crust rises to top).
After done, pour more juice evenly over top.

title: homemade barbecue
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.

title: easy peach dessert
directions: Use 2-quart baking dish.
Melt butter.
Pour peaches and juice in dish.
Put dry cake mix on top of peaches.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 or 50 minutes.

title: barbecue dry rub mix
directions: Process until the bay leaf is pulverized and mixture is thoroughly blended.
Store in an airtight container at room temperature for up to 3 months.
Makes about 1/2 cup.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in two 8-inch pie crusts for 30-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until brown, 30 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients except bacon strips.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until pepper and onion are tender.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.
Casserole will freeze well.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix the pretzels and margarine and spread. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: dutch sweet bread(koch)
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil the water, raisins, butter, molasses and spices.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and let set for 3 or 4 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: talorina casserole
directions: In morning, brown meat; pour off grease.
Add corn, tomato sauce, chopped green pepper, pimentos, olives and mushrooms.
Cook about 1 hour.
In evening, add cooked noodles.
Put in casserole dish.
Add grated cheese on top.
Heat in medium oven until hot through and cheese melts.
Serves 10.

title: verna hoffman's oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients until creamy.
Then add next 3 ingredients and blend well.
Stir in oats.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese come to room temperature in a bowl.
Stir in cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Blend on low speed.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Stir in chipped beef. May roll ball in nuts if desired.
Chill for 8 hours.

title: thalhimers' richmond room spoonbread
directions: Place cornmeal in a mixing bowl.
Pour boiling water over. Mix well.
Stir in flour, milk, eggs, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat with a wire whisk until smooth.
Pour into a lightly greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven until firm and golden brown, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kid's munchies
directions: Pop the popcorn according to package directions and cool.
In a 6-quart or larger bowl, mix together all the ingredients.
Serve immediately.
To store, divide into the desired portions and store up to five days at room temperature in sealed containers or resealable, zipper-top bags.
Makes 24 cups.

title: yam corn bread
directions: Mix flour, corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. Combine eggs, milk and oil in large bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add yams; beat until well blended.
Add dry mixture, stirring only until moistened.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with butter.

title: coach's carrot cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in a greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: stuffed ham rolls
directions: Rinse frozen asparagus under cold running water to separate. Place one frozen stick of crab meat and 2 asparagus spears on narrow end of each ham slice.
Roll up and secure with a wooden pick.
Place rolls, seam side down, in an ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking dish.
Cook uncovered in 350° oven about 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook uncovered until crab meat is hot and cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
tags: thin slices fully cooked smoked ham

title: breakfast or brunch casserole
directions: Put bread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with cheese, sausage and mushrooms.
Mix eggs, milk, onion and dry mustard.
Pour this mixture over other ingredients; chill overnight.
Mix together one can mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk and pour over chilled mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let set 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: molasses cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and stir well. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Pour mixture into two round cake pans, greased well.
Bake at 300° for 35 minutes or until done.
Let cool.
Put apple butter between layers.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix thawed hash browns, soup, butter or margarine, onions, salt and pepper and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Fold in sour cream. Put in 9 x 13-inch buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle rest of Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt bert's custard rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling, salted water; boil 15 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Drain water from rice.
In 2-quart casserole, beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla, raisins and lemon rind. Add 2 cups milk to drained rice.
Add to egg mixture.
Blend well.
Sprinkle nutmeg and bits of butter over pudding.
Place in deep pan and fill pan almost full of water.
Bake 1/2 hour; stir. Bake 1 more hour or until a silver knife comes out clean.
Cool. Bake at 325°.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all together.
Should be soupy.
Cook, uncovered, for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Fry ground beef and onion together; drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Simmer 1 hour.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients and pour over shrimp in roasting pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes or until done, stirring every 7 to 8 minutes.
This is a good way to fix jumbo shrimp.

title: rice pudding
directions: Gradually stir milk and egg into pudding mix in saucepan.
Add rice and raisins.
Stir over medium heat until mixture just comes to a boil.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice.

title: cranberry sparkle punch
directions: Beat cranberry sauce until smooth.
Add orange juice and lemon juice.
Blend until combined.
Add ginger ale.
Serve over ice in punch bowl.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Layer ingredients; do not mix together.

title: kansas city ribs
directions: Simmer for approximately 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place ribs on hot grill and sear on both sides. Brush sauce generously on both sides of the ribs and cook for an additional few minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix usual way.
Cream Crisco and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly with milk to cream mixture.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't open oven until time is up.
Place on bottom rack of oven to cook.

title: judi's chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in pie pan; cover with chili.
Sprinkle scallions and green pepper on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: cheese and mushroom quiche
directions: Saute onion, butter and mushrooms.
Add flour and mix well until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients into 9-inch pie plate using Pillsbury pie crust and bake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.
For variation, you can use less mushrooms and add fresh veggies!!

title: syrup cookies
directions: Put oil, sugar and egg together; mix well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to sugar mixture, mixing until blended.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: old time buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and margarine. Add eggs and beat. Stir in buttermilk and vanilla flavoring. Pour into pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Add 1 cup coconut, if desired.

title: broiled deviled burgers
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; add beef and mix well.
Split buns and toast uncut surfaces under broiler.
Spread cut sides with beef mixture.
Broil 3 inches from heat for 6 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef and rice
directions: Mix soy sauce, brown sugar and seasonings.
Add beef and let stand 10 minutes to marinate.
Stir-fry beef in hot oil until brown.
Add vegetables.
Stir-fry until tender but still crisp. Mix broth and cornstarch and add to skillet.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Serve over prepared rice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Dissolve peach
Jell-O with 1 1/2 cups water.
Pour over peaches in
baking
dish.
Sprinkle cake mix over peaches.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Use any favorite biscuit recipe, adding cornmeal to the dry ingredients.
Knead lightly and roll out to 1/8 inch thickness. Spread sausage evenly on dough.
Roll up like a jelly roll about 2 inches in diameter and wrap in wax paper or aluminum foil until chilled.
Slice about 1/4 inch thick and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 450° until golden brown.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in cold water in small pan, adding boiling water.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until clear; set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy, add salt.
On high speed gradually add sugar until peaks form.
Add vanilla. Gradually add cooled cornstarch mixture, beating as you add it. Beat until peaks form.
Pile on pie.
Bake at 300` until lightly brown.

title: super macaroni salad
directions: Cook and cool the macaroni.
Mix together with all the remaining ingredients.
Chill 4 hours.

title: fish stew - peruvian
directions: In a large saucepan, brown bacon and dice.
Stir in bell peppers and onions and saute until wilted.
Add potatoes, corn, tomatoes, Ro-Tel, water, lemon juice and seasonings.
Bring to a boil and then reduce to a simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add fish and cook 5 minutes or until fish is done.

title: lemon crumb dessert
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in hot water.
Add lemon and juice.
Chill until thick like egg whites.
Place in mixing bowl and add chilled milk; beat until fluffy.
Mix margarine and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Press into two 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Reserve about 1/2 cup of the wafers.
Spoon jello mixture into pans. Sprinkle crumbs.
Set until firm.
Keep cold.
Cut and serve.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Dissolve unflavored gelatin in water.
Add gelatin and blend with a whisk until bubbly.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour into a greased bowl or mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Invert onto a plate and serve with crackers.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Make dough using flour, salt, baking powder, shortening and egg, beaten in cup with enough water to make 3/4 cup.
You may need more if dough is too stiff.
Make a real soft dough.
Roll out on a floured cloth, then cut into thin squares.
Drop into boiling broth.
Add black pepper and 1/2 stick butter.
When done, add chicken.

title: mexican cheese dip(appetizer)
directions: Chop onion and crush garlic in bowl.
Add butter.
Melt in microwave 60 seconds or until limp.
In large frypan, melt American cheese (on low) with other ingredients.
Add onion and garlic.
Simmer over low heat until everything is melted together, about 2 hours.
Serve hot with corn chips.

title: hilda's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon and orange extracts.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Refrigerate dough for 1 hour for easier handling.

title: italian chicken
directions: Skin and debone chicken breasts.
Pound a little.
Beat egg. Dip in bread crumbs.
Put margarine in frypan and brown chicken. Line chicken in glass baking dish. Add to the top the black olives (split), green pepper (sliced) and sliced mushrooms.
Put chicken broth in frypan.
Pour in baking dish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: cream of crawfish soup
directions: Saut garlic and onion until clear.
Slowly add flour, stirring constantly.
Slowly add broth, stirring constantly.
Whisk in the half and half until the mixture thickens.
Stir in Tony C's seasoned crawfish and green onion.
Serve immediately.

title: crunch top apple pie
directions: Mix apples with 1/2 cup sugar, 1/4 cup flour, salt and cinnamon.
Put in pie shell.
Combine sugar, graham cracker crumbs, flour and walnuts.
Put over apples.
Drizzle melted butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandpa gilbertson's prune bread
directions: The way I mix it (Grandpa), I put eggs, sugar, juice, pulp, milk and vanilla and beat these just so they are well mixed. Sift in 2/3 of the flour and all soda.
Put in lukewarm margarine.
Put in rest of flour.
Mix gently; do not beat too much. This recipes makes 7 loaves.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes and take out of pans.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, mustard, celery seed, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add potatoes, eggs, onion, celery and pickle; mix lightly. Chill before serving.

title: spicy black bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor until smooth. Serve with pita chips and crackers.

title: hash brown potato casserole(serves 15 to 20 people)
directions: Melt margarine and potatoes and put into a 13 x 15-inch baking dish.
Mix the rest of ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: uncooked brownie nuggets
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a saucepan.
Stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Boil one minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well mixed and drop quickly onto waxed paper.

title: crock-pot steak-n-gravy
directions: Boil water.
Dissolve Lipton soup mix in water.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Stir well.
Set aside.
Brown steak.
Place steak and soup mixture in crock-pot.
Cook on low 7 to 8 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes and corn.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend butter, salt and sugar.
Add eggs, lemon juice, spice, potato pulp and hot milk.
Place in pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach madeline
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, place both packages of spinach. Microwave on High for 15 minutes.
Drain and set aside spinach liquor.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Mix spices and baking powder with flour; sift.
Mix well. Then add berries and other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 55 to 60 minutes in a tube pan.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add spaghetti sauce in large bowl.
Combine eggs, oregano, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Beat with mixer for several minutes. In 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, center 4 uncooked noodles.
Pour 1 cup sauce, then half of the cheese mixture. Place 4 more uncooked noodles over cheese, then 1 cup sauce. Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups Mozzarella.
Layer 4 more uncooked noodles and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle water around the edges. Cover with foil.

title: cheese thins
directions: Mix pepper and margarine (cream).
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add cheese and Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Press with fork dipped in ice water.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, bone and cut into small pieces.
Butter 13 x 11-inch glass dish.
Line the bottom of the dish with the meat. Mix all of the remaining ingredients. Pour mixture over the meat. Sprinkle chips on top (optional).
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: ruby's stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of peppers and remove seeds, etc.
Parboil peppers in lightly salted water about 2 minutes.
Cook rice by directions on box.
Mix ground beef, cooked rice, chopped onion, Worcestershire, salt, pepper and tomatoes.
Stuff peppers.
Place in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Spread 1 can crescent rolls on bottom of pan and brown at 350°.
Melt Velveeta and cream of chicken.
Brown hamburger.

title: apple-peanut bread
directions: Mix
flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Cream shortening, sugars
and
egg together.	Combine with flour mixture and	orange juice.
Blend well.
Add raisins, nuts, apples and orange rind. Bake in loaf pan at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar together; set aside.
Blend eggs, strawberries, oil and pecans.
Combine all ingredients.

title: pan fried corn pones
directions: Pour boiling water over meal; mix to combine.
Stir in egg and bacon or cracklings.
Shape in pones by pressing between hands and fry on both sides until golden brown, about 10 to 15 minutes. Serve hot.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Boil 1 cup water and pour over ingredients.
Bake at 365° for 1 hour.

title: mary's pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar for 10 minutes; add eggs (one at a time). Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla, lemon, orange, almond, coconut and pineapple flavoring. Add flour and whipping cream. Bake in a "cold" oven, 300°, for 1 1/2 hours. Use a tube pan.

title: zucchini al forno
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Top and tail the zucchini and cut lengthwise into 1/2 inch slices.
Coat the slices in flour and fry until they are crisp and golden.
Oil a circular ovenproof dish and arrange the zucchini slices like the spokes of a wheel.
Beat together the eggs, milk, salt, pepper and half the cheese.
Add the basil leaves and pour over the zucchini.
Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake for 15-20 minutes.

title: cherry-pecan dessert
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add 2 tablespoons of mix to the cherries.
Add the sugar to the beaten egg and beat for 5 more minutes.
Stir in dry ingredients, butter, almond extract and cherries.

title: diabetic smack roons
directions: Beat egg whites with baking powder until stiff, but not dry. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Dough may be divided into four portions and 5 cookies made from each portion.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 20 cookies (40 calories per cookie).

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, salt, egg and butter.
Mix the soda and water together.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Beat well.
Add bananas and flour and mix.
Pour into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350° until toothpick inserted comes clean.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar; mix well until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip, fruit cocktail, cottage cheese, nuts and jello. Chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In saucepan, cook green pepper strips with garlic and butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Heat, stirring now and then.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Pour boiling water over jello; stir to dissolve.
Add cold water and cranberry relish.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in walnuts and celery.
Chill in a 2-quart mold until set.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Add green onions and garlic salt.
You can mix pecans in cheese ball or roll cheese ball in pecans.
Chill 30 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add onion, celery, peppers and garlic.
Cook and stir for about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add tomato sauce, water, parsley, salt, pepper, bay leaves and shrimp.
Simmer for 10 minutes (you may need to add additional water) and serve over hot cooked rice.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Add milk gradually until yeast is dissolved. Add sugar, shortening and eggs.
Beat.
Add
flour
and salt gradually to mixture until you can knead
the
dough.
Let
stand in a warm place to rise double
in
size.
Roll
out to 1/4-inch; spread with melted oleo.
Sprinkle
with
brown
sugar,
cinnamon and ground nuts.
Roll and cut.
Let rise until light.	Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: hearty oats 'n wheat loaves
directions: Generously grease two 8 x 4 or 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups bread flour, oats, salt and yeast; blend well.
In medium saucepan heat water, corn syrup and butter until very warm (120 to 130°F).
Add warm liquid and eggs to flour mixture.
Blend at low speed until moistened; beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
By hand, stir in whole wheat flour and rye flour to form a soft bough.
On floured surface, knead in up to 1 cup bread flour until dough is smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap and cloth towel. Let rise in warm place (80 to 85°F) until light and doubled in size, about 1 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Pour 1/2 package of small marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over marshmallows.
Mix dry cherry Jell-O with cherry pie filling.
Pour this mixture over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Marshmallows come to the top and cherries to bottom.
Do not have to ice.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, flour and oleo well, then add buttermilk. Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: spicy hominy
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 12 x 9-inch glass baking dish. Do not drain hominy.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, or until all liquid has been cooked out.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Combine the sugars, butter, eggs and orange juice.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add nuts and oats to flour mixture. Mix all preceding and add marmalade and blueberries.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and let set for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cool in the pans.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook 1/4 c wild rice, 25 minutes, drain, set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet; drain off excess fat. In bowl, combine ground beef, green pepper, onion, tomato, salt and pepper; mix well.
Place this in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add squash and 1/2 of cheese.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over squash.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake until squash is done.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add soda, baking powder and vanilla.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain.

Stir in 3/4 of salsa. spread remaining salsa in oblong casserole dish and top with 3 corn tortillas, meat mixture, beans, 1/2 of Cheddar cheese, 3 corn tortillas, sour cream, chili and remaining 1/2 of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carol's meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Mix beef with beaten egg, milk, tomato sauce, onion, green pepper, salt, pepper, oregano, paprika, bread and Ritz crackers, crumbled.
Place in a quart baking dish.
Top with tomato catsup; cover.
Cook on High for 10 or 11 minutes, using temperature probe to 180°.
This makes 6 servings.

title: unbelievable fruit pie
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk.
Pour on top of margarine.
Pour in pie filling.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Press cookie dough with pizza pan.
Bake according to directions on package; cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar and milk with whisk.
Add the Cool Whip.
Spread in large cookie.
Add coconut, chocolate chips, peanut butter chips and chopped nuts. Cut into small pieces.
Refrigerate until served.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with 1 stick margarine.
Spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat eggs, confectioners sugar and 2 sticks margarine in mixer bowl about 15 minutes.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas. Drain pineapple and pour small amount of pineapple juice over bananas.
Add pineapple.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with pecans and cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir in sugars, oil, zucchini and vanilla.
Combine all dry ingredients and stir into zucchini mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: microwave chicken and vegetable casserole
directions: Layer sliced potatoes in large glass casserole dish.
Season with 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Cover and microwave on Full power for 5 to 6 minutes.
Layer onion and green beans on top of potatoes. Cover and microwave on Full power for 5 minutes.
In the meantime, in a small bowl, mix tomatoes, Worcestershire, remaining pepper and garlic powder.
Layer cooked chicken and tomato mixture on top of vegetables.
Cover and microwave for 15 to 18 minutes on Medium power.
Let stand 5 to 6 minutes before serving.

title: delicious salmon
directions: Heat olive oil in frying pan over moderate heat.
Drain salmon and tomatoes, saving juice from both.
Saute onions.
Add flour and mix smoothly, letting it brown slightly Pour liquid from salmon and tomatoes into onion mixture.
Stir in parsley, oregano, soy sauce and tomatoes.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Lower heat and place salmon in single pieces of 8 inches in pan.
Add celery and green pepper around salmon.
Do not stir.
Simply place sauce on top and simmer 6 minutes.
Serve with vegetables, sauce and salmon wedges.

title: crazy cake
directions: Sift together in an 8 x 8 1/2-inch pan the sugar, flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Make 3 holes.
In the first hole, pour the oil.
In the second hole, pour the vinegar.
In the third hole, pour the vanilla.
Pour 1 cup of cold water in pan and mix; don't beat.
Preheat oven and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Don't grease pan.

title: roast marinade
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Marinate roast, brisket (up to 5 pounds) overnight.
Roast in a covered pan approximately 1 hour per pound at 300° or in a crock-pot until tender.
Vegetables cooked along with the meat are wonderful.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter, stir in soup and tomatoes and mix well.
Place thinly sliced potatoes in baking dish and cover with the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.
When done, cover with cheese and cook until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and steam to soften leaves.
Saute onion, garlic and green pepper before mixing with meat.
Mix together the meat, rice, seasonings, onion, pepper and garlic.
Roll meat into separate cabbage leaves.
Place in large pot.
Add water, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cover; bring to a boil.
Turn down heat when it comes to a boil.
Put on simmer for 1 hour, or until done.

title: meal for two(low-fat)
directions: Take skin off. Boil chicken until it is no longer pink. Debone and add vegetables and a little water.
Cook until tender. When almost done, add a dash of soy sauce.

title: french dressing(mrs. joe alfson)
directions: Put all together in salad bottle or jar.
Shake good and refrigerate.

title: nana's pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Whip eggs.
Whip eggs into sugar, Karo syrups and vanilla.
Add melted butter and salt.
Place chopped pecans in bottom of 2 pie shells.
Pour mixture on top of nuts.
Bake at 375° until brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Ritz crackers.
Pour in a casserole dish and top with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grace faucheux's ash wednesday crepes
directions: Beat the eggs first.
Add the baking powder, water, pinch of salt and flour. Beat well.
Grease skillet with a little oil and pour 1/4 cup mixture.
Move pan to spread.

title: apple-walnut cake
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix at low speed after each addition, just until blended.

Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan. Combine finely chopped apple and next 3 ingredients; spoon over batter in pan, leaving a 1/2-inch border around center and outer edges.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes on a wire rack.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack. Drizzle with Cream Cheese Glaze.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: One 10-inch cake.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir sugar, syrup and water in pan.
When sugar dissolves and comes to a boil, add butter.
Stir often after syrup reaches 230°, add nuts at 280°, stir to hard crack at 305°.
Remove from heat and add soda; mix well.
Pour out on two cookie sheets. Stretch ends with fork.
Pour into pieces as soon as possible. Makes 2 1/2 pounds.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs.
Sift together the dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
Fold in nuts and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Melt caramels in top of a double boiler with the margarine and milk.
Stir and set aside.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of this batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
When baked, pour caramel mixture over evenly and sprinkle chocolate chips evenly over caramel layer.
Put nuts on top of chips.
Add remaining batter and bake for 30 more minutes at 350°.
Cut in bars when cooled.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add hamburger, salt and pepper. Crumble bouillon cube.
Brown.
Add tomato soup and cream of mushroom soup.
Let simmer for 5 minutes.
Add sour cream.
Cook noodles.
Put layer of sauce in oblong dish, then layer of noodles, a layer of sauce, ending with sauce.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix butter, powdered sugar and 1 cup flour and pat in bottom of square baking dish; bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Thaw potatoes, then mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish for 1 1/2 hours.
Bake 45 minutes covered and then for 45 minutes uncovered.

title: crazy cake
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Lightly grease 9 inches from saucepan.
Put ingredients in mixing bowl in order given, then mix together. Beat 3 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes. Let cool and frost with desired frosting.

title: jolloff rice of west africa
directions: Make a stew with onion, corned beef, pepper, salt and oil. Add the parboiled rice into the pot of stew with all the ingredients.
Allow to simmer for 30 minutes.
Add water according to demand until the rice is well cooked, approximately 45 minutes. Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: best gingersnaps
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, soda and spices.
Cut in shortening like pie mix.
Stir in molasses and egg.
Shape into 2 rolls in floured wax paper.
Refrigerate.
Slice 1/4-inch thick. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle top of each cookie with sugar before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and dry jello.
Mix in oranges and pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and stir until mixed.
Chill.

title: sugar-free pumpkin pie
directions: Beat pumpkin, milk and eggs in medium bowl.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in preheated oven, 425°, for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted near center comes out clean, about 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a food processor.
Spread in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Layer rest of ingredients.
Garnish with the black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tangy vegetable salad
directions: Drain juice from all cans.
Prepare whatever amount of the celery, green pepper and pimento you wish to add.
Cut onion in rings.
Combine all.
Heat sugar, vinegar, water and oil until it boils.
Pour over the drained vegetable mixture and chill overnight.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus, peas and water chestnuts, in order listed. Pour can of undiluted soup over layers, then a layer of Velveeta Cheese.
Melt the oleo and mix into 1 1/2 cups Town House cracker crumbs. Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and slice.
Chop celery, onion and pimentos.
Add together.
Cook bacon; cool and crumble.
Save bacon grease.

title: scallop potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Slice small onion and green pepper.
Mix the can of cream of celery soup with milk.

In a large baking dish, arrange a layer of potatoes, a few slices of onion, a few slices of green pepper, part of soup mixture, slices of American cheese; continue until dish is about 1/2-inch from the top.
Garnish with garlic, Cajun seasoning and salt.
Bake in a covered dish for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix all and bake in prepared skillet or 8- or 9- inch square pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt margarine.
Stir all ingredients together. Pour in pie shell and bake at 300° for 50 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries, peaches, pears and pineapple thoroughly and combine in a large bowl.
Blend together remaining ingredients. Fold into fruit.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Mix beans and soup.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Place French fried onion rings on top. Bake for another 5 minutes.

title: coconut caramel dessert
directions: Combine flour, 3/4 cup butter and 3/4 cup pecans.
Mix together and press into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Melt 1/4 cup butter, coconut and 1/2 cup nuts.
Cook over low heat until coconut browns.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, condensed milk and whipped topping.
Layer on crust:
cream cheese mixture, 12 ounces caramel sauce (I use more caramel sauce) and coconut mixture.
This makes 3 layers.
Cover and freeze.
Serves about 20.

title: grandma winkler's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, milk, cinnamon, cocoa, baking powder, soda, oats and flour, blending well.
Add nuts and raisins last.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: krum kake
directions: Mix ingredients into batter.
Heat iron over stove until water beads on iron.
Pour small amount of batter on iron; cook 10 seconds on a side.
Remove and roll up.
Serve with ice cream.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Pat shrimp dry.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add oil, lemon juice, garlic and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add shrimp and green onion.
Cook until shrimp turns pink, about 5 minutes.
Blend in parsley, lemon peel and dash of hot sauce.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: creates its own crust(coconut pie)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add milk and flour, blending well; add coconut.
Pour into a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Combine sugar and egg; add molasses and shortening.
Sift together flour, salt, cloves, baking soda, cinnamon and ginger. Combine the two mixtures and mix well.
Form in balls and dip tops in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients in order given.
Pour in ungreased 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over filling. Pour melted butter over top.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until knife comes out clean when inserted halfway from center.
(For an 11 x 15-inch pan, bake at 375° for about 40 minutes.)
Serve warm or cold, plain or with whipped topping.

title: tangy slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, carrots and onion in a large bowl.

title: karo fudge
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add cocoa to butter.
Add sugar, Karo and milk.
Cook slowly and stir often until it will make soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Heat until slick and loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered pan and mark into squares.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning and mayonnaise.
Spread bean dip in bottom of casserole dish.
Then layer the mayonnaise and taco seasoning mixture, sour cream, salsa and cheese.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes. Ready to serve.

title: nestle quik cake
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Bring oleo, Nestle Quik and water to a boil and pour over sugar and flour mixture.
Mix and add eggs, buttermilk, soda and vanilla to other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken, broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into cubes. Set aside.
Mix soups, broccoli and the sage and onion stuffing all together into large bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish, then top with Cheddar cheese and bake at 425° for 1/2 hour.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Melt butter in pan (large frypan). In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, milk, eggs and salt. Stir until combined. Pour batter into pan and bake for 30 minutes until edges have risen and are golden brown and center is set. Remove from oven and dust with confectioners sugar. Serve with fresh fruit/berries. Serves 6.

title: betty's strawberry ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until white.
Beat in sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line in ice cream freezer.
Freeze in ice cream freezer.

title: doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add milk, sugar, salt, egg, shortening and half of flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add rest of flour.
Knead about 5 minutes and put in good greased bowl.
Let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise again for 30 to 45 minutes.
Drop in grease at 375°.
Remove when golden brown.
Drain and roll in sugar, cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large pot, melt butter with oil.
Stir in onions and salt. Cook over low heat until onion rings separate easily.
Sprinkle onions with flour and stir.
Add beef stock and simmer partially covered for 30 to 40 minutes.
Add some Kitchen Bouquet for color, if desired.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine in saucepan oleo, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper to cool.

title: beef parmesan
directions: Trim meat and cut in pieces.
Dip pieces in egg.
Roll in cheese and bread crumbs.
Heat oil in skillet; brown meat.
Add onion and cook until tender over low heat.
Stir in next 5 ingredients and gradually add hot water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Add scrapings, any leftover cheese and bread crumbs.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Serve over noodles.

title: santa claus sour cream cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add remaining ingredients.
Wrap dough in wax paper and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch and cut out.
Place on sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch these cookies closely so the bottoms don't overbake.
Cool before decorating.
Double or triple recipe for best results and more cookies.

title: baker's 5 minute creamy coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened in mixer bowl; beat in sugar. Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut, Cool Whip and extract.
Freeze until firm.

title: kahlua
directions: Split vanilla bean in 4 pieces.
Mix ingredients in 2-quart dark jar.
Cover tightly.
Allow 30 days to age, shaking from time to time.

title: russian tea cookies
directions: Blend sugar and margarine; add the rest of the ingredients. Roll into walnut size balls and press with thumb to make indented cookies.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cookie sheet does not have to be greased.
These are good coated with powdered sugar.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in water until tender.
Melt margarine and add flour.
Finally, add Velveeta and melt.

title: swiss venison steak
directions: Trim excess fat from venison.
Cut venison into serving sized pieces.
Pound venison to 1/4-inch thickness.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge venison in flour mixture.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Can be served with whipped cream.

title: johnny knows it
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients in a large skillet; add soups and tomato puree.
Cook noodles as directed; drain.
Add to soup mixture. Pour into 2 baking dishes.
Top with cheese and olives. Freezes good and is good leftover.
Serve with garlic toast and salad.

title: grandma's mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni noodles according to package directions. Drain. Saut onions in butter or margarine. Add tomato soup and cheese. Stir until cheese melts. Combine soup mixture with noodles. Stir well. Let sit for 5 minutes before serving. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Pop corn and pour into large bowl.
Add nuts and M&M's.
Melt marshmallows and butter together.
Pour over popcorn mixture and mix well.
Pour into tube pan that you have sprayed with Pam. Press mixture down and let cool.
Turn on a plate and slice.

title: au gratin casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion in cooking oil for about 10 minutes. Add box of au gratin potatoes and cheese packet, along with hot water.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Add vegetables and cheese; cook until vegetables are tender.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini, covered,
in boiling, salted water, 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Set	aside.	Cook
onion
and
green pepper in butter until
tender,
but
not	brown.	Remove from heat. Stir in mushrooms,	dry spaghetti mix, water and tomato paste. Mix well.
Gently
stir
in
zucchini
and	Mozzarella cheese. Turn into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish (or 1 1/2 quart shallow casserole).
Sprinkle
with
Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: old fashioned peach crisp
directions: Place peaches in baking dish; may sprinkle with sugar if tart. Mix rest of ingredients and put on top of peaches.
Bake 375° until done.

title: basic sweet rolls
directions: Combine the yeast and water and let it stand for a few minutes.
Cream the butter, sugar and salt.
Add the beaten eggs and juice from the half lemon.
Add the milk to the softened yeast and combine with 3 cups flour, beating until smooth.
Then mix this into the creamed mixture, adding enough more flour to make a medium dough.
Knead the dough on a floured board until smooth. Raise until doubled in a greased, covered bowl.
Shape as desired. Let rise again.
Bake.
After cooling, frost with icing, if desired.

title: chicken kiev
directions: After depositing lobster into boiling water, return water to boiling.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes per pound.
Make certain not to overcook so fat does not escape into the water.

title: forty percent bran rolls
directions: Add baking powder to the first few cups of flour.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water and stir.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain vegetables and chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients, except butter and crackers; pour into a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and butter that have been mixed together. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: barbecued biscuits
directions: Brown ground beef, onions and seasoning.
Drain.
Mix in barbecue sauce.
Flatten biscuits and put in muffin tin.
Fill each biscuit with meat mixture.
Top each biscuit with cheese 5 minutes before done.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: instant coffee chiffon pie
directions: Mix Knox gelatine, 1/4 cup sugar, coffee and salt together thoroughly in top of double boiler.
Beat 3 egg yolks and 1 cup milk.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Cook in boiler until gelatine dissolves completely, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes. Chill to room temperature.

title: aunt lucy's yellow angel food cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until bubbly.
Add sugar that has been sifted 5 times.
Beat until stiff.
Add water.
Sift flour and baking powder together 5 times.
Add to egg mixture, folding in slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake in large tube pan as for white angel food.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Reduce heat after 20 minutes.

title: basil butter
directions: Mix together until smooth

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes (cut up), tomato sauce, bouillon cube (crushed), parsley, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and basil.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Mix cottage cheese, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, 1/2 teaspoon salt and oregano.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put layer of noodles, sauce, cheese and cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat.
Save sauce for top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon; remove skin and bones. Combine all ingredients and chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken breast and stove top dressing casserole
directions: Cook Stove Top according to directions on box.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut chicken breasts in 2-inch pieces and lay over dressing.
Spread soup over top of chicken (do not dilute soup). Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a large shallow pan (cookie sheet).

Heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt until bubbly around edges. Continue cooking for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in soda until foamy. Pour over popped corn and stir to coat. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain juice into pan.
Add one egg yolk (beaten), 2 tablespoons of sugar and enough flour to thicken.
Heat until fairly thick; let cool.
Add to pineapple and marshmallows.
Whip cream until real stiff, then add pineapple and marshmallows.

title: basic white bread("james bieard on bread")
directions: Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm milk and sugar to proof.
Put remaining warm milk, margarine and salt in a large bowl.
Stir in flour, 1 cup at a time, with wooden spoon.
After 3 cups flour, add proofed yeast.
Continue stirring flour in until mix is rather firm, about 4 to 5 cups.
Knead until no longer sticky.
Put in buttered bowl to rise until double, in warm dry place, about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: coffee can bread(makes two 1 pound cans)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in water and let stand 15 minutes or until foamy looking.
Add other ingredients.
Combine with a mixer until too stiff.
Add rest of flour; knead into smooth ball (5 minutes).
Divide in half.
Grease coffee cans and plastic lids.
Put dough in cans.
Let rise until lids pop off.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bottom sounds hollow.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: Mix together and press into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: easy cherry tarts
directions: You will need 24 baking cups.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons butter and stir in flour.
Add salt, pepper, sugar and onion powder.
Mix.
Add sour cream.
Fold into green beans.
Top with cheese and cornflakes mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients, then put in refrigerator to cool.
You may freeze all or part of it.
Mmmm good!

title: donuts
directions: *I use Equal and cinnamon-sugar for a sugar-free coating.

title: nellie's carrot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water and cream cheese; refrigerate until partially set.
Add carrots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Fold in Dream Whip and refrigerate.

title: great pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Cream the margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix all well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and pumpkin. Stir in morsels.
Drop by 1/4 cup dough onto cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes until lightly brown at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: lemon chicken with thyme
directions: In a plastic or paper bag combine flour, salt and pepper. Shake to mix.
Add chicken, shake and coat lightly.
Remove chicken and save flour mixture.
In large skillet warm 1 tablespoon olive oil; add chicken; brown on one side.
Add second tablespoon olive oil; turn chicken and brown on other side.
Transfer thicken to plate.
Add margarine to skillet.
Cook onion 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in reserved flour.
Add broth and 2 tablespoons of lemon juice; bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat and cover (5 minutes).
Put chicken on plate.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon juice to skillet; stir and pour over chicken.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients and chill overnight in refrigerator.
Roll and cut.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: hot and spicy egg spread
directions: Mix the eggs and butter together until smooth and creamy.
Add the Worcestershire sauce, celery seed, parsley, red pepper and salt.
Mix well.
Serves 12.

title: quick buttermilk rolls
directions: In a large bowl combine 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda.
Mix well.
In a saucepan heat buttermilk, water and shortening until warm.
Add to flour mixture.
By hand, gradually stir in enough remaining flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth and elastic (about 5 minutes).
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place until light and doubled in size (about 20 minutes).

title: hearty italian spaghetti
directions: Prepare sauce mix, adding tomato sauce as directed on package. Brown beef in skillet.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Place spaghetti on platter or in large, shallow bowl.
Top with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sweet-and-sour meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients for meatballs; shape into twenty (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes.
Or cook in ungreased oblong pan, in 400° oven until lightly brown, 20 to 25 minutes. Drain fat.

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Wash	and
dry
potatoes
and arrange in single layer on a rimmed cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve
hot or warm with cheese, ham, bacon, sour cream and chives (scallions).

title: zippy chicken
directions: Heat soup and cheese.
Gradually add other ingredients.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Place in greased casserole and cover with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: "kvasaky" crock pickles
directions: Combine
salt,
vinegar and water; boil and cool.
Peel medium size cucumbers and put into a gallon jar.
Add garlic, red
hot peppers,
shallots and dill.
Pour cooled brine over this
and let
set
out
on
cabinet top until milky (about 3 days).
Then put in the refrigerator.
They are ready to eat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and orange together.
Add sugar and let stand for 1 hour.
Prepare jello in 1 1/2 cup water instead of 2 cups.
Combine all ingredients and let gel.

title: great leftover chicken casserole
directions: In
a greased
casserole
dish,
layer
chicken,
bread filling and gravy (small
amount of chopped onions if desired) until dish is full.
Top
with bread crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° until top
is
brown.
Served
with
side dish of peas or salads this is a good, fast meal.

title: hearty baked beans
directions: Place beans, celery, mango, onion and hamburger in a large baking dish.
Mix together molasses, ketchup and spices.
Stir into beans.
Place bacon on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: mamaw's coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni-corn casserole
directions: Grease a casserole dish and mix all ingredients right in dish. Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook 15 minutes more. Check to see if done. If not, cook 15 minutes more.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: tuna tasties
directions: Break the bread into very small pieces.
Mix the bread with tuna, egg and peas.
Spray the muffin tin with Pam and press the tuna mixture into muffin tin.
Grate cheese to sprinkle over each muffin.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: mom's homemade chili(the best)
directions: Cook slowly, stirring constantly, to keep from sticking to pan.
Cook about 30 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: 1. In a mixing bowl combine hot water and jello. Stir until jello is completely dissolved.
2. Add raspberries and applesauce. Stir until mixed
throughly.
3. Refrigerate overnight then top with cool whip and
serve the next day.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bring to a boil, then beat until it thickens.
Put in pan to cool.

title: tuna salad
directions: Break tuna into large flakes.
Mix tuna, celery, onion and parsley.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Serve on lettuce. Makes 8 servings.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in 3 layers.
Let cool.
Mix the brown sugar and enough water together in a heavy saucepan to stir.
Put on stove and stir until mixture boils to ball stage (a drop of mixture into a cold cup of water and ball forms).
Take off heat. Add the margarine.
Beat with electric mixer until thick, about 3 minutes.
Add the diced oranges and mashed bananas to this mixture.
Stir well.
Put a few fork holes in top of each layer of cake. Spoon evenly over each layer. Sprinkle coconut.
Prepare each layer and repeat on next. Stack and keep in refrigerator.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup oil.
Pour 1/4 cup oil into pan or an iron skillet works best.
Preheat pan or skillet and pour batter into hot grease.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash and mash.
Add soup, sour cream, onion and pimento.
Mix stuffing and margarine.
Put a layer of crumb mixture in the bottom of a large 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Pour in squash mixture.
Top with rest of the crumb mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: grandmother's cake
directions: Mix cake mix according to directions.
Add coconut and pecans. Mix well with mixer.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (Pam pan). Bake 35 minutes.
When done, while hot, punch holes all over cake. Pour Eagle Brand over cake.
Let cool.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and beat again, then add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Divide into 2 portions.
Leave one plain and add chocolate to the other.
Chill, then roll out both portions into very thin oblong sheets.
Lay the chocolate on top of the white.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill again, then cut into thin slices and bake on greased cookie sheets in oven at 375° to 400°.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Set aside 1/2 of cheese.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: strawberry french toast sandwiches
directions: Spread each sandwich with cream cheese and jam.
Combine eggs, milk and salt in a shallow dish.
Dip sandwiches on both sides. Brown in margarine.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve immediately.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, brown sugar, flour and crackers and half the cheese.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with remaining cheese and reserved juice.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until cheese it thoroughly melted.

title: oyster pie
directions: Saute celery and onion in oil.
Grease large casserole dish with butter.
Layer with crackers, half of oysters, celery, onion and part of butter.
Sprinkle pepper over this.
Blend 2 eggs with chicken soup and milk.
Pour half of mixture over layers.
Repeat layers again.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 325°.
Beat 2 eggs.
Remove the casserole from oven and top with eggs.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix; bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: debi's broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli heads only into small bite size pieces. Chop onion and crumble bacon. Add shredded cheese. Mix together in large bowl.

title: florence's orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add cream cheese and pineapple. (Beat with mixer or wire whisk.)
When cool, add Cool Whip and place in refrigerator until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in medium saucepan; drain.
Add taco mix and water.
Drain kidney beans and add to mixture.
Cook on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Add tortilla chips; mix well.
Spread mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese melts.

title: pecan balls
directions: Preheat the oven to 300 degrees.
Combine the butter and sugar in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping the bowl occasionally.
Add the vanilla, beating until blended.
Add the flour and pecans gradually, beating well after each addition.
Shape into balls, using a small scoop.
Arrange 1- inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or just until the cookies begin to brown around the edges.
Cool on the cookie sheet for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack to cool slightly.
Sprinkle the warm cookies with the confectioners' sugar. Makes 42 cookies.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Press crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread cooked sausage evenly over rolls.
Pour beaten eggs over sausage; sprinkle with garlic powder.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Save Oreo crumbs.
Cream the cream cheese and margarine together and set aside.
Mix vanilla pudding and milk together for 2 minutes.
Fold the cream cheese mixture into the pudding mixture and mix well.
Fold Cool Whip into the pudding/cream cheese mixture.

title: parmesan chicken bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese and seasoning in shallow dish.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture to coat both sides.
Melt margarine in baking dish in oven.
Add chicken turning to coat both sides with margarine.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix the crushed graham crackers, white or brown sugar and soft butter.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Mix together coconut and condensed milk; put on top of crust mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Frost with melted chocolate chips.

title: hot mexican cornbread
directions: Make cornbread as usual and add the corn, onion and pepper. Bake at 450° for about an hour.

title: banana french toast with blueberry sauce
directions: In a blender or food processor, mix bananas, milk and cinnamon until very smooth. Pour mixture into a shallow bowl. Heat a nonstick griddle over medium-high heat and brush lightly with oil. Dip bread into banana mixture and cook until lightly browned on both sides.

title: mexican casserole
directions: In skillet, brown ground chuck; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning mix.
In a bowl, melt cheese; stir in undrained tomatoes and green chilies.
In a lightly greased medium casserole dish, place the meat mixture.
Top with cooked rice.
Spread cheese mixture over top.
Sprinkle crushed tortilla chips over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the ingredients in the order listed.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° until done.

title: pigs-in-blankets
directions: Flatten dough; wrap hot dogs with dough.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Bake on cookie sheet for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Put onion, celery, green pepper and fresh mushrooms in first. Cook until about half done.
Add rest of vegetables and cook until done.
Do not overcook.
Let vegetables be crisp.

title: bacon wrapped water chestnuts
directions: Wrap chestnuts in individual strips of bacon.
Roll up and stick a toothpick in each.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven at 350° until bacon is done (not crispy).
Take out of oven.

title: apple-nut coffee ring(makes 2 rings)
directions: This also freezes well.
Great for Christmas.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers over the top; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Dip chicken into egg and then into bread crumbs, coating thoroughly.
In a medium skillet, heat olive oil. Cook chicken in oil until done and well browned.
Pour spaghetti sauce into 11 x 17-inch baking dish.
Place chicken on sauce and top with Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and lightly browned.
Makes 4 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell (you can use a pie shell prebaked).
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 325° and bake until center is firm.

title: coconut moist cake
directions: Follow directions on box.
After baking, let cake set 10 minutes.
Take a fork and poke holes throughout the cake.
While warm, pour condensed milk all over cake.
Take a spoon and mix Cool Whip until fluffy, then spread Cool Whip on cake as desired. Sprinkle coconut flakes over cake; refrigerate until ready to be eaten.

title: sia chili
directions: Brown ground meat with onions and garlic.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add flour and chili powder mixture.
Cook over low heat several hours if time permits.
Add beans and heat thoroughly.
Serves 10.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Crust:
Unfold crescent rolls.
Lay flat and press down in jelly roll pan.
Bake according to directions on package.

title: corn spoon
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry; beat egg yolks.
Stir corn meal and salt into scalded milk, beating hard.
Cook for a few seconds over low heat, stirring like thick mush.
Blend in butter and corn, then baking powder.
Fold in yolks, then whites.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.

title: macaroni pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni. Brown hamburger and onion. Add salt and pepper. Mix meat, macaroni, pizza sauce and sugar. Add oregano. Place 1/2 of mixture in casserole. Add a layer of cheese, then another layer of each.
Top with pepperoni slices. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fig cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350°.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: wassail
directions: Heat together all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Strain and pour into serving container. Serve hot.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Cream butter; cream eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: boiled shrimp a la bob
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
In a pot which holds at least 6 quarts water, put on to boil.
Add salt, cut up onion, garlic and celery and add to water.
Cut lemon in quarters; squeeze in water and add.
Add bay leaf, seasoning bag and cayenne pepper (this is to taste, depending how spicy you want shrimp).
Bring to a boil and boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Add shrimp; time exactly 3 minutes, then turn fire off.
Let shrimp soak for 20 minutes.
Drain and either eat hot or refrigerate.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add brown sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, chips and vanilla.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in shortening. Add rice and tomato sauce.
Cook all about 30 minutes and season with salt and pepper.
Cook over
low heat.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in order.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oven-fried fish
directions: Dip fillets into eggs.
Lightly coat with bread crumbs. Arrange fish in a single layer on a well-greased shallow baking pan.
Combine batter and lemon juice; drizzle over fish.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: vanilla wafer salad
directions: Line a small pan (6 x 10-inch) with vanilla wafers.
Boil together margarine, egg yolks and sugar until thick.
Let cool and add pineapple and nuts.
Pour over vanilla wafers.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 8 or 10 ice cubes and stir until melted.
Pour over custard.
Refrigerate until set.

title: lazy wife cake
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients well;
add 2/3 of water and mix again, then
add
remaining
water and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Frost with peanut butter icing.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and 1/4 cup tomato sauce.
Heat cooking oil in medium-size skillet, tilting to coat the sides. Press meat mixture into skillet evenly.
Cover tightly and cook over low heat 30 to 40 minutes, until meat is done.
Drain juices from meat into a saucepan and add remaining tomato sauce.
Heat. Turn meat loaf onto a platter, cover with the sauce and garnish with chopped parsley.

title: honey oatmeal bread(make with kitchen aid mixer)
directions: Place 5 cups flour, oats, salt and yeast in a bowl. Attach dough hook. Turn to speed 2 and mix for 15 seconds. Combine honey, water and margarine or butter in saucepan.
Heat to 120° to 130°. On speed 2, slowly add warm liquids to flour mixture.
Mix for about 1 minute. Add eggs and mix an additional 1 minute. Continuing on speed 2, add remaining flour, 1/2 cup at a time, until dough clings to hook and cleans sides of bowl, about 3 minutes.
Knead on speed 2 for 2 minutes or until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in a
greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk (about 1 hour).

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas. Combine all ingredients. Mix well. Spoon batter into well greased 9x5x3 inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 min. or until top is golden brown and splits.

title: fork cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar well; add egg and beat again.
Add flour and soda to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla and lemon. Chill at least 4 hours or overnight.
Form balls about the size of a small walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
You can roll in sesame seed or nuts, brown sugar or white sugar before baking.

title: chili dog sauce
directions: Slowly brown ground beef with onion and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes. This sauce freezes well.

title: *chop suey
directions: Fry meat, then add soup stock or water, 1 tablespoon of the soy sauce and vegetables.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Make paste of remaining soy sauce, molasses and flour.
Add to mixture in skillet; stir.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve with rice or chow mein noodles.

title: carlene's chili
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Add pkg. chili seasoning to drained ground beef.
In large saucepan, saute onions with can of Rotel tomatoes.
Add ground beef, beans with the juice, tabasco chili mix and bay leaf.
Let simmer at least 1 hour on medium heat.

title: cheese and tomato delight
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
Crush tomatoes in juice and pour over noodles in baking dish.
Add cheese.
Stir and mix well. Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Measure juice liquid; add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Mix in.
Put in refrigerator until jiggly.
Beat jello.
Add pineapple and oranges.
Add whipped cream.
Mold.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients and make into balls.
Cook on broiler pan at 400° until done.

title: marinated wind wing tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in large pieces.
Add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours; remove garlic.
Makes 4 servings.

title: four layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix together flour, oleo and nuts.
Press into bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let cool.
