title: wild rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice as package directs.
Chop onion, mushrooms, green pepper, cheese and margarine and mix with evaporated milk.
Mix all together and cover and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Take cover off and brown.

title: easy chicken calzones
directions: Separate crescent rolls into triangles.
Mix tomato sauce, chicken, and cheese.
Spoon this mixture on to wide end of each crescent triangle.
Fold pointed end over filling and pinch seams to seal.
Brush with beaten egg.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.
Serve and enjoy!

title: prune, date or raisin and nut whole wheat bread
directions: Beat the eggs until light, then add the sugar and beat until thick.
Add the milk.
Mix dry ingredients and toss the nuts and fruit in, combine liquids.
If needed, add 1 or 2 spoons of milk to soften.
Oil a large bread pan or two small ones.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Small pans may take 10 minutes less.

title: modern brunswick stew
directions: Skin and cut up chicken into serving pieces.
In Dutch oven, combine chicken, water, broth, celery, onion, green pepper, garlic, parsley, thyme, Worcestershire sauce, hot pepper sauce, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Add frozen vegetables and cook another 30 minutes.
Return chicken to pot.
Let simmer a few minutes longer.
Serve hot with corn muffins or hot biscuits. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hershey's icing
directions: Bring to a boil and pour over cake.

title: mom's oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins; mix well.
Add flour sifted with soda, salt and cinnamon. Beat well.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: stuffed cornish hens
directions: Cook rice, using package directions; cool.
Add remaining ingredients, except Cornish hens.
Toss lightly to mix.
Salt inside of Cornish hens and stuff with rice mixture.
Roast at 375° for 1 1/2 hours (roast loosely covered for 30 minutes, then 60 minutes, uncovered) or until done.
If desired, occasionally baste with melted butter or glaze the last hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown round steak with next 5 ingredients. Simmer 1 hour. Add green pepper strips over top. Cook 10 minutes, covered. Mix cornstarch and soy sauce well; add to steak. Stir well. Serve over rice.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: In large bowl, mix well flour, sugar and salt with fork; add shortening.
Mix well until crumbly.
In small bowl, mix water, vinegar and egg; beat.
Add to flour mixture, stirring until moistened.
Divide dough into 5 sections.
Shape each into flat circle.
Wrap each in plastic wrap or waxed paper.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Lightly flour each side of patty, then roll out on lightly floured surface.
For baked pie shell, place in pie plate; prick bottom and sides.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 (9-inch) shells.

title: ro-tel chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken (save stock).
Boil vermicelli in broth; drain.
Saute bell peppers and onion in butter.
In a large bowl, mix vermicelli, peas and mushrooms.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix in the chicken and Velveeta cheese (cut into small pieces).
Mix together and bake in casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes a lot.

title: tuna royal
directions: Place tuna, soup, celery, onions, salt, water and part of the noodles in casserole dish and cover.
Put in oven and cook for 25 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 can of noodles over the top before serving.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken breast; cool and chop fine.
Add remaining ingredients to chicken breasts and mix well.

title: cheatin' bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a Bundt pan, melt butter in oven. Remove rolls from container, but do not unroll.
Place in Bundt pan.
Pinch edges together well, forming a circle of dough.
Bake for 30 minutes until golden.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch pan, 4 to 5 inches deep.
Pour into pan first the nuts.
Over top of nuts place cherries, pineapple and cake mix.
Next slice margarine over cake.
Do not mix or stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Spoon out or dump onto a flat surface.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: chili with rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat on medium-high heat.
Drain fat.
Add seasoning mix to the meat.
Stir in water, beans and tomato sauce.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in corn.
Return to boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Serve with shredded cheese and/or sour cream. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Mix all ingredients (batter should be thin but should stick to fillets).
Batter should be a little thinner than pancake batter. Add more beer, if needed.
Soak fillets in batter approximately 15 minutes.
Fry in hot oil.
Oil is hot enough if a drop of batter comes to the top of the oil right away.

title: creamy cheese cake
directions: Melt cream cheese in saucepan. When melted, add sour cream and beat thoroughly.
Slowly add eggs, sugar, vanilla and heavy cream. Beat very thoroughly (several minutes).

title: delicious broccoli soup
directions: Finely chop broccoli and onion (food processor is a great help and timesaver too).
Saute in butter until tender.
Stir in milk and soup.
Cook mixture until thoroughly heated.
Add Velveeta and stir until melted.
Ready to serve.

title: vickie's famous salsa
directions: Mix the Pace picante sauce and 1 can of tomatoes in a bow. Chop the onions and cilantro and add the picante sauce. Add cheddar cheese and garlic and mix once again. Then refrigerate for at least 1 hour.

title: christmas pudding
directions: Cream the shortening with brown sugar until fluffy in a large bowl.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together. Add to batter alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in candied fruits and walnuts.
Pour into a well-greased 8-cup mold.
Cover mold with foil or double thickness of waxed paper.
Fold foil down tightly or fasten with string to hold tightly if waxed paper is used.

Place on rack or trivet in large pan; pour in boiling water to 1/2 the depth of pudding mold. Cover large pan tightly and steam for 2 1/2 hours or until long, thin skewer inserted in center of pudding comes out clean.
Add more boiling water during steaming as needed.
Cool for 5 minutes, then unmold on serving plate.
Spoon 1/2 cup Orange Crystal Sauce over top. Garnish with holly and green and red candied cherries, plus a walnut half, threaded on wooden pick, if desired.
Cut in wedges and serve with additional Orange Crystal Sauce.

title: sausage-bisquick balls
directions: Mix together well.
Squeeze into little balls size of marbles. (Can be frozen.)
Put on baking sheet in 375° to 400° oven.
Turn once to bake evenly (not more than 30 minutes).
Serve hot.
May be served with a toothpick or not.
Makes about 77 balls.

title: layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating one in at a time. Add milk and vanilla mixed together.
Mix in sifted flour and mix well.
Pour into four greased and floured cake pans and bake in moderate 350° oven until done.
(For thinner layers put less mixture in the pans.
I get 6 to 7 thin layers from this batter.) Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: white wine sauce
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium heat; stir in flour until smooth.
Cook and stir 1 minute more.
Gradually whisk in stock and milk until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook and stir until sauce thickens and bubbles for one minute.

title: red beans and rice(bayou country favorite)
directions: Wash beans, soak overnight and drain.
Cover beans and all ingredients with cold water.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer until done.
Serve over rice.
Large link smoked sausage, added the last 30 minutes, gives delicious seasoning and makes a complete meal with hot fluffy rice and tossed salad.
Serves 6.

title: barbecue roast beef for sandwiches
directions: Cut leftover cooked roast beef opposite the grain so you don't have long strings of meat.
Put in electric frying pan and add diced onions and almost cover with water.
Cook 2 to 3 hours, until it falls apart easily, adding more water if necessary.
With water almost cooked out of it, add brown sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce and a little mustard.
Cook another 30 minutes.
Place in warmed hamburger buns.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onions; add pork and beans, brown sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, salt and pepper and add bacon on top of beans and bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear leaves into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, oranges and onion rings; toss with Tangy Orange Vinaigrette Dressing.
Serve immediately to four or six people.

title: kim's breakfast
directions: Grease pan.
Place Tater Tots, vegetables, meats, seasonings and cheese in pan.
Cover with beaten eggs.
Bake at 350°.

title: oyster dressing with crust
directions: Soak about 6-inches of bread in oyster juice. Cook meat and onions down in covered pan until grease is out (about 1 hour). Add parsley and oysters.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Toss.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
This is good with soup or as an appetizer.

title: rolled out cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and beat. Mix dry ingredients together.
Add to first mixture, 1 to 2 cups at a time (hard to stir).
Can add up to a 5th cup of flour as needed.
Chill 20 to 30 minutes.
Roll out and cut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake.

title: double chocolate mocha trifle
directions: Prepare brownies according to directions. Cool completely. Whisk pudding mix into milk until mixture begins to thicken. Dissolve coffee granules in warm water. Add to pudding mixture, mixing well. Fold in whipped topping. Cut brownies into squares. Chop Heath bars. Layer 1/3 of the brownies on bottom of bowl. Top with 1/3 of the pudding mixture and then top with 1/3 of chopped Heath bars. Repeat layers 2 more times. Chill 30 minutes before serving. Garnish with Cool Whip and grated chocolate, if desired.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Blend milk, egg and salt; mix with macaroni and spread evenly on cookie sheet.
Spread spaghetti sauce evenly on top of macaroni.
Top with pepperoni, peppers, tomatoes, onions, mushrooms and seasonings.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until macaroni is hot and set. Let stand 5 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon to roll dough balls in. Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt; stir in. Add vanilla. Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: condensed milk flan
directions: To make caramel, cook sugar on low heat until brown and thick, then cool.
Break eggs without making foam.
Mix 2 cans of milk with one can water and add eggs without mixing.
Add vanilla and salt.
Strain over caramel pot.
Cook in double boiler for 1 hour.

title: rice cooker sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into small pieces and brown in skillet on stove. Place rice, browned sausage and all other ingredients in rice cooker.
Cook until cooker turns off, about 30 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Combine boiling water, shortening, sugar and salt. Cool to lukewarm and add yeast, softened in lukewarm water.
Mix to smooth batter with 1 cup flour.
Stir in potatoes and eggs.
Let rise 2 hours or until light and bubbly.
Add remaining flour to make soft dough.

title: cuernavaca casserole
directions: In small mixing bowl, mix the corn meal, salt and soda.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Blend in corn meal mixture.
Pour into a 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish (greased).
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: caramel crackers
directions: In saucepan, mix margarine, butter and sugar.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Place crackers on cookie sheet.
Pour sugared mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cut into triangles while still warm.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in 1/4 and roll in sugar mixture and place in greased Bundt pan.
Melt the 1 1/2 sticks butter, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla; pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350°.
Let bake for 1 hour.

title: turkey and ham loaf
directions: Put turkey and ham into a large mixing bowl.
In heavy saucepan or skillet, melt butter and cook onion and parsley until onion is limp.
Turn off heat and stir in croutons or bread crumbs, tossing to mix.
Pour in chicken broth and add the whole mixture to the turkey and ham.
Sprinkle in seasonings, cream and eggs; mix lightly, but well.

title: polish bread
directions: Mix the buttermilk and 1/2 teaspoon baking soda together and set aside.
Mix the butter, sugar, eggs and sour cream together and set aside.
Mix the flour, 2 1/4 teaspoons baking powder, salt, nutmeg and raisins together and set aside.
Fold flour mixture into butter mixture.
Add buttermilk and whiskey.
Bake at 300° in a greased and floured tube pan for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cornbread dressing(never fails)
directions: Cook fatty portions of chicken to make broth or use canned broth.
Cook onions and celery in butter until tender.
Crumble cornbread in a large mixing bowl.
Add stuffing mix.
Add all liquids and mix well.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: country oven beef
directions: Combine ingredients in a 6-quart Dutch oven in this order of layers:
beef, onions, carrots, tapioca, bread crumbs, mushrooms, salt and pepper, tomatoes, basil and garlic, bay leaf and wine. Cook, covered, in a 300° oven for 4 hours.
Do not stir or disturb in any way.
Great served over rice or noodles.

title: angel hair pasta with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat 1/4 cup olive oil over low heat in saucepan.
Add garlic. Cook until it softens, not browned.
Add tomatoes, nutmeg, salt, pepper, sugar and cook uncovered over medium heat about 10 minutes.
Add parsley.
Remove and keep warm.
While sauce is cooking, line a cookie sheet with foil.
Spread onions and toss with 1/4 cup of the olive oil.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Place about 3 to 4 inches from preheated broiler.
Cook until onions are wilted, only slightly browned, about 5 to 6 minutes.
Carefully stir around a bit while broiling.
Cook pasta in pot of boiling water until barely tender.
Drain and rinse.
Place equal portions of pasta on plates in center of sauce.
Top with broiled onions and sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: oven chicken dinner for one
directions: Wash skinless chicken breast. Lay on square of foil. Layer other ingredients on top of chicken. Salt and pepper and lay on oleo. Sprinkle with water. Fold up foil and seal. Lay in pan. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Spray a Bundt pan with nonstick spray.
Sprinkle pecans in bottom of pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour batter over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test for doneness; toothpick will come out clean when inserted in middle of cake.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix and add more flour if needed.
Roll thin; cut with small biscuit cutter.
Put pecan half in center of each biscuit. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° until lightly browned.
Put biscuits on brown paper to absorb grease.
When cooled, dust with powdered sugar.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water and beef bouillon cube.
Stir.
Add spices.
Stir and cover.
Cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
When done pour over cooked noodles.

title: no-pecan pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar.
Warm beans.
Stir in oleo and vanilla.
Add coconut.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°, then lower temperature to 350° and bake another 20 minutes until done.
(Tastes like pecan pie.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and bulgur in butter until brown.
Add remaining ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: company pie
directions: Mix well and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add salt to remaining 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add flour and buttermilk mixtures alternately.

title: pickled red beet eggs
directions: Boil together all ingredients except eggs for 10 minutes. Pour over peeled hard-boiled eggs.
Refrigerate for a day or 2 before serving.

title: night before breakfast goodies
directions: Chop all sausage and fry; drain meat.
Wipe out excess oil from pan.
Return cooked sausage to pan.
Top with sliced cheese. Cover; allow cheese to melt on low heat.
Stir.
Split muffins and place on a cookie sheet.
Spread sausage and cheese mixture on top of muffin halves.
Place in refrigerator, uncovered, for 2 to 3 hours.
After set, put in Ziploc freezer bag.
When ready to eat, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: nine layer salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put layer of lettuce and add other vegetables in layers on top of lettuce.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits.
Put chopped tomatoes on top if you wish.
Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in greased jelly roll pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: beef boat
directions: Mix together all ingredients except bread.
Make night before and refrigerate.
Use 2 loaves Italian bread; curve out one for boat and cut up rest of bread into cubes for dipping into dip.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw broccoli in refrigerator overnight.
Mix all ingredients. Pour in loaf dish or pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: thanksgiving pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: To slightly beaten egg yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar, pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Cook until thick in double boiler.
Soften gelatine in cold water.
Add to hot pumpkin mixture.
Mix thoroughly and cool.
When it begins to thicken, fold in mixture of egg whites and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Pour in shell and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Mix soup, eggs, onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Add to drained broccoli.
Pour in baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing.
Cover top of mixture with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini
directions: Wash, slice thinly, then pare turnips.
Place them in layers in a baking dish.
Dredge them lightly with flour.
Sprinkle with salt, freshly ground pepper and sugar.
Dot turnips with butter.
Nearly cover with milk.
Bake the dish in a hot oven at 400° until the turnips are tender (about 1 hour or more).
The last 15 minutes, add 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: greek chickpeas salad
directions: Combine cheese, mustard, salt, oil, lemon juice and pepper in container of electric blender; whirl until smooth.
Combine chickpeas and onion in large bowl.
Pour dressing over and toss. Refrigerate; may be prepared several days in advance.
Just before serving, add parsley; toss.
Spoon into lettuce lined salad bowl.

title: good punch
directions: Add 4 cups sugar with 4 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Dissolve Jell-O in mixture.
Then add remainder of water and all the rest of the ingredients except ginger ale. Freeze.

title: graham banana pudding
directions: Whisk together first 5 ingredients over medium-to-low heat in large saucepan, stirring constantly. Cook until thickened and boil 1 to 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in margarine (butter) and vanilla. Layer in 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole dish with graham crackers, bananas and pudding. Repeat layer as needed. Cover and chill. May top or serve with 2 cups whipping cream mixed with 3 tablespoons sugar, beating until soft peaks form.

title: cup custards
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar and enough milk to fill 4 to 5 custard cups.
Dust nutmeg on top.
Place in pan of hot water in a medium oven for 40 minutes or until a knife comes out clean. Makes 4 to 6 cups, depending on size of eggs.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix meat, bread crumbs, eggs and milk.
Shape into loaf.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and water; baste ham loaf several times while cooking.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate covered popcorn
directions: Stir over
medium
heat
until it passes the ball test. Drop small amount of chocolate sauce in cup of cold water.
If it forms a ball, it's ready.
Pour over already popped, salted and buttered popcorn.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In casserole dish, combine macaroni, cheese, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add enough milk to cover or 3/4 full in dish.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: honey sesame tenderloin(serves 3 to 4)
directions: *Can buy in health food store - GNC.

title: coconut cake(from 1879 cookbook)
directions: Bake in cakes an inch thick and spread with icing, having grated coconut stirred in, pile one on the other, allowing a little time for drying off.
In making the icing, reserve some plain for the outside of cake; finish off by sprinkling on the prepared coconut.

title: todd homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in gallon freezer container.
Freeze as directed.

title: bake beans
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from grease.
In bacon grease, saute peppers and onions.
Add beans to mixture, then add the remaining ingredients.
Crumble the bacon and add to the ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Grease baking dish with butter.
Layer it with broccoli, cheese and Ritz crackers.
Mix butter and crumbs.
Put on top of casserole.
Pour 1/2 cup sweet milk over the top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: kale soup
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil; add carrots, potatoes, water and kidney beans.
Add tomatoes and juice; add kale and let simmer for about 45 minutes, until carrots and potatoes are soft.
Add vinegar, liquid smoke and hot pepper sauce.
May substitute spinach for kale.

title: swiss steak
directions: Salt and pepper tenderized steak; dip in flour.
Brown in oil in frying pan until browned on both sides, then remove from pan and lay in oblong baking pan.
Then take your sliced onion, bell pepper and stewed tomatoes and put on top of browned meat; season again with salt and pepper.
To the remaining oil in frying pan, mix at least 2 to 3 teaspoons of flour with oil until brown.
Pour flour drippings over meat, onion, pepper and tomatoes in pan.
Add about 2 cups of water to pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with white rice.

title: porky's revenge from lewis grizzard
directions: Combine everything except the pork roast in a saucepan and cook 30 minutes over medium-low heat.
Pour over roast and marinate 12 hours or overnight.
Roast pork.
Cook reserved marinade 30 minutes, until thick.
Slice meat and pour sauce over.

title: cornbread upside-down dinner
directions: Brown ground meat, bell pepper and onion and drain.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole dish and top with Cornbread Mixture.

title: impossible lasagne pie(the pie that does the impossible by making its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inch).
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
Mix the beef, herbs, tomato paste and 1/2 cup Mozzarella; spoon on top.
Beat the milk, baking mix, eggs, salt and pepper for 15 seconds on high.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into cooked pie crust. Top with cool whip.

title: curry chutney chicken salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, chutney, curry powder, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and mix in almonds.
Chill before serving.

title: seven-layer cake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs to make crust.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips, chocolate chips and coconut on crust.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over whole mixture, covering well.
On top, add walnuts and press down.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Mixture will get golden brown around edges.

title: super lasagna(good)
directions: Cook lasagna according to package directions. Drain. Brown beef in large skillet in oil with onions and garlic. Add tomato paste, tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, oregano, bay leaf, basil, parsley, 1/8 teaspoon pepper and 1 1/2 cups water. Simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cottage cheese, egg and remaining salt and pepper. Grate Mozzarella cheese.
Arrange layers of noodles, cottage cheese mixture, beef mixture and cheese in a 13 x 9-inch pan, ending with Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate cake supreme
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) or 1 (13 x 9-inch) pan and set aside.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix for two minutes with electric mixer.
Stir in boiling water by hand.
Mix will be thin.

title: grandma's egg noggreeley, colorado
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, vanilla and mix well.
Add milk and mix.

title: texas yum yum cake
directions: Blend together first three ingredients with pastry blender. Pat into large Pyrex dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Mix together 1 cup Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix vanilla pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on top of cream mixture.
Mix chocolate pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Spread on top of vanilla pudding. Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top of mixture.
Sprinkle with toasted pecans and one small Hershey bar, curled.
Place in refrigerator.

title: anniversary chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Saute chicken 4 to 5 minutes per side until lightly browned.
Place in 9 x 13 dish.
Brush each with teriyaki sauce, then spoon on Ranch dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese, onion and bacon bits.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until chicken is cooked through and juices run clear.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Chop onion and slice squash into a crock-pot. Add tomatoes, chicken broth, corn, rice and water. Cook 1 or 2 hours in crock-pot. Serve with avocado cubes, shredded cheese, and tortilla chips crumbled on top.

title: orange sweet potatoes
directions: Arrange potato slices in a baking dish.
Sprinkle generously with brown sugar and dot with bits of butter and orange peel. Pour over the orange juice and scatter 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and a little bit of paprika
over the top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes, then remove cover and continue baking until brown and nicely caramelized.

title: corn casserole
directions: Put all ingredients into casserole and bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: microwave broccoli chowder
directions: In 2-quart microwave bowl, combine broccoli, onion and water. Cook, covered, on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Stir twice, breaking broccoli.
Stir in soup, milk, cheese and pepper.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 7 to 9 minutes, until well heated, stirring twice.
Top each serving with chopped peanuts.
Serves 4.

title: lo-cal vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and serve with fresh vegetables such as cucumber and square slices, carrot and celery sticks, tomato wedges and cauliflower and broccoli florets.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat margarine until creamy; add preserves and lemon juice, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in coconut and oats.
Shape mixture into balls.
Press center of each with thumb and fill with preserves.
Refrigerate.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: impossible quiche tarts
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease 18 muffin cups, 2 1/2 X 1 1/4 inches.
Beat sour cream, baking mix, milk, eggs and worcestershire sauce until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed or 1 minute with hand blender.
Spoon about 2 Tbsp. into each muffin cup.
Mix remaining ingredients; sprinkle 1 Tbsp. over batter in each cup. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 12 - 15 minutes.
Loosen sides of tart from pan; remove from pan. Refrigerate any remaining appetizers.

title: puffy pancakes
directions: In a pie pan, melt butter in the oven.
While melting butter mix the rest of the ingredients together.
Pour mixture into melted butter.
Bake in a 425° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until done.

title: raisin pie
directions: Place raisins in 2 cups water and bring to a boil. Add Equal, butter and salt. Mix cornstarch with small amount of water and stir until dissolved. Pour into raisin mixture and cook until thick. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Top with second pie shell and secure edges of pie. Bake at 350° until done.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage and onion in skillet.
Combine with entire ingredients and pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Measure flour, salt and sugar into gallon jar (will bubble to four times its volume).
Stir in yeast and cold water.
Cover with cheesecloth.
Let stand in warm place (80° to 90° is ideal), stirring down daily, 3 or 4 days.
It should have pleasantly sour odor.
Starter is ready. Use at once or store tightly covered in refrigerator in quart jar.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients; press down firmly.

title: potato filling balls
directions: Saute celery and onions in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and
shape
into
balls with an ice cream scoop.
Put balls into	a buttered casserole and may pour more butter over top of	each
ball.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Using real butter makes them so delicious!!

title: ski lodge lamb 'n tomato soup
directions: Heat oil in skillet and brown lamb, turning often.
Remove cubes and place in slow cooker.
Saute onion in skillet, stirring until onion is translucent, but not brown.
Add all other ingredients to slow cooker.
Cover pot.
Set on low.
Cook 6 to 8 hours or until lamb and barley are tender.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Layer as listed.
Spread mayonnaise mixture over top.
On top, put shredded cheese (I use Cheddar). Cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: skillet breakfast
directions: Place bacon and potatoes in a nonstick skillet.
Cook over medium heat 12 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Stir in onion and chili powder.
Pour eggs over mixture.
Cook until mixture is set.
Cut into wedges.

title: chopped preserved figs
directions: Mix sugar and water and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add chopped figs and cook slowly, stirring gently every 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook until 2 drops syrup comes off spoon at one time, approximately 1 hour but may take longer.
Seal and boil in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Test for seal and store in cool place.
(This recipe may be doubled or tripled.)

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Lightly grease an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Drain artichoke hearts (in water) and cut into small pieces.
Lay in bottom of dish.
Drain marinated artichoke hearts and chop into small pieces.
Place on top of plain artichokes.
Spread chopped chilies across artichokes.
Lightly coat with mayonnaise.
Cover with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and apples in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside for a few minutes.
Mix dry ingredients with apples.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 50 minutes in 300° oven.
Top with frosting or Cool Whip.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Bake cake in 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 15 minutes.
Let cool. Blend milk, cream cheese and pudding.
Pour on cooled cake. Sprinkle crushed pineapple over pudding.
Then spread Cool Whip. Refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Soften margarine and cheese.
Add flour and mix well.
Make small balls, size of marbles.
Press these into small muffin tins.

title: wild rice whatsis
directions: Cook wild rice with the juice of the beans and enough water to make up 3 1/2 cups.
After rice has cooked 20 to 30 minutes, add onions and celery.
When vegetables are almost done, stir in green beans, mushroom soup (and meat and water chestnuts).
Bring to boil again and serve.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter treats
directions: Mix sugar and Karo together.
Bring to boil (until sugar has melted); stir continually.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter until dissolved, then add Rice Krispies.
Pour into greased Pyrex; cut in squares (cut while still warm).

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix together.
Double recipe for large salad.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Using an electric mixer, beat margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir using mixer.
Add coconut, vanilla and pecans.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into three greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Leave cream cheese and Cool Whip out for 2 hours.
Into a small rectangular baking dish, mix with 1/4 pound melted butter and graham cracker crumb mixture to make crust.
Blend together 1 cup powdered sugar and 1 large package of cream cheese.
Spread over crust.
Slice 3 or 4 bananas over cream cheese filling. Spread pineapple over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip; sprinkle walnuts and place strawberries on top and cool in refrigerator overnight.

title: burger bundles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix meat, soup mix, egg, pepper, water and bread crumbs.
Press into bottom of 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Prick meat mixture with fork.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until desired doneness.
Place Velveeta slices over meat.
Bake 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt.
Cut into 24 squares.
Can be used for sandwiches or as meat with vegetable and salad.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften Cream Cheese.
Mix with all ingredients except crab until smooth and creamy.
Stir in crab.
Make a day ahead to give spices time to mix well.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Put into a 10-inch spring-form pan that has been lined with aluminum foil.
Press down.
Chill for about 15 to 30 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix rice, water, mushroom soup and celery soup in large casserole dish which has been greased.
Place cut up chicken on top of soup and rice mixture.
Salt and pepper lightly.
Top with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek.

title: easy chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk until thickens.
Pour into crust. Chill.
Cover with whipped topping. Sprinkle with chopped peanut butter cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour soup and milk over chicken. Combine stuffing, water and melted butter over the top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Can be made day ahead.
Do not freeze.

title: orange bread(yields 30 muffins or 2 loaves)
directions: Quarter a Valencia orange; remove seeds.
Put it through a blender or processor until very finely chopped (nearly pureed). Don't remove peel; "trust me!"
Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, orange and oil.
Add all dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Pour into muffin tins or 2 large loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or 1 hour for loaf.

title: vidalia onion cobbler
directions: Combine cornbread mix with egg and milk.
Pour into large greased skillet.
Cover with onion slices or pieces.
Mix sour cream, corn, salt, and pepper.
Pour over onions.
Bake at 400° for about 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple praline pie
directions: Mix together the apples, 1/2 cup brown sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Spoon into pie shell.
Top with second crust.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large saucepan.

Add onion, salad dressing and tomatoes; simmer and stir until liquid is evaporated. Combine beef, sausage, bread crumbs, milk, eggs, 1/4 cup grated Romano cheese, 1/4 cup chopped parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Mix well; brown in remaining butter in skillet.
Add meat to tomato mixture.
Add the tomato paste, water, sugar, 1/4 cup parsley, fennel seed, basil, 1/4 cup Romano and remaining salt. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: southern pecan oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and butter and let stand until butter is melted.
Stir in sugars, eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Put into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef flour enchiladas
directions: Cook ground beef well.
Drain.
Mix into cooked beef, onion, lettuce, carrots, potatoes and chopped olives.
Add 1 cup of shredded cheese and garlic powder.
In separate bowl, blend cumin, oregano, water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add can of enchilada sauce. Heat the sauce in pan.
Dip tortillas into saucepan, one by one. Add beef to dipped tortillas and start rolling them.
Place on tray and garnish with shredded cheese and sliced olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cremecicle fudge
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Then add chocolate chips and marshmallow cream.
Mix well.
Reserve 1 cup.
Add to first mixture orange flavoring, yellow food coloring and red food coloring.
Mix well and pour in buttered dish, then drizzle the reserved cup over top and swirl with knife.

title: salmon salad tart
directions: Or use your own rich biscuit dough.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and cook 1 minute.
Add milk and continue cooking, stirring until thickened.
Add cheeses and cook until cheese melts and mixture is smooth.
Cook and drain broccoli according to package instructions.
Stir cheese mixture into broccoli.
Turn into a buttered 1/2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Preparation Time:

title: taco salad
directions: Fry ground beef; drain and mix in taco seasoning.
Cool.
Just before serving, toss lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, chilies and beef. Crunch up Doritos and stir in.
Pour dressing on to taste.

title: chicken fingers
directions: With milk, mix all ingredients to a pancake batter texture. Dip chicken in batter and deep fry in oil, turning until golden brown.

title: sunday rump roast
directions: Place roast, onion soup mix and mushroom soup on foil.
Place potatoes and carrots around roast; seal foil tightly.
Bake for 3 to 4 hours using rack in roasting pan; season with salt.

title: salsa
directions: Mix tomatoes, chili powder, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Chop green pepper, onion, carrot and jalapeno pepper with juice in blender.
Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown ground beef. Drain. In a slow cooker, combine cooked beef, tomato sauce, beans and tomatoes and cook on high until heated through, about 1 hour. Top with shredded cheese and serve with cornbread.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake by directions on cake mix box and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Poke holes in warm cake with wooden spoon handle. Pour 3/4 can Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Drizzle hot fudge topping that has been warmed in microwave over cake. Refrigerate. Top with creamy Cool Whip and Skor or Heath bits.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Melt margarine and mix well with crackers.
Grease casserole dish.
Place layer of broccoli, top with cheese, then top with crackers.
Repeat again, ending with crackers.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread applesauce cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pat into small cookie pan.
Bake at temperature on box for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oliebollen dutch doughnuts
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop batter by teaspoonfuls into hot, 375°, fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper; roll in powdered sugar. Makes 30.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown hamburg in large frypan with green pepper, garlic powder and onion powder.
Drain fat from pan.
Add taco seasoning mix. Add chili.
If desired, add hot pepper.
Add the cut up cheese and cook until cheese is melted, stirring as cheese melts.
Serve with nachos.
Great reheated.

title: teriyaki chicken wings
directions: In large shallow dish or plastic bag, combine all ingredients except chicken; mix well.
Add chicken.
Cover; marinate in refrigerator 6 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°; arrange chicken on rack in aluminum foil-lined shallow baking pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: quick and easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove bones and excess skin.
Add bouillon cubes to broth and bring to boil.
Divide each biscuit into 4 pieces (use scissors) and drop into broth.
When mixture thickens, add chicken.
Boil noodles separately and drain.
Add to chicken mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream margarine; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, peanut butter, vanilla extract and corn syrup; beat well.
Add oats, soda and salt, stirring well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop dough by 1/4 cupfuls, 4 inches apart, onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes (centers of cookies will be slightly soft).
Cool slightly on cookie sheets; remove to wire racks and cool completely.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Combine the yeast, water, salt and sugar.
Stir in the flour a little at a time until the dough is stiff enough to knead.
Knead dough until it becomes soft, about 5 minutes.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour.
Shape pretzels and place on prepared cookie sheet.
Brush with mixture of 1/2 cup water and 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 400° until lightly brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Drain kraut.
Use your own judgment on amount of pepper, carrots and onions and mix with kraut.
Add sugar.
Mix well. Refrigerate.
The longer it sets in refrigerator, the better it is.

title: phyllis' parmesan tater wedges
directions: Wash and quarter potatoes.
Put in cold water.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Put potatoes and dry mixture in a bag and coat.
Lay potatoes in melted margarine and bake at 375° for 1 hour, turning once.

title: party punch
directions: Put sugar and Kool-Aid in gallon jug.
Add enough hot water to dissolve.
Next, add pineapple juice to jug.
Finish filling jug with water.
Freeze.

title: mississippi cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: bucket bread
directions: Mix raisins, dates, soda and water; let cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla, flour and salt.
Blend and add pecans.
Bake in 3 (1 pound) coffee cans or 6 (16 ounce) cans (sprayed with Pam) for 1 hour at 350°.
Freezes nicely.

title: preston's dirt bombs
directions: Mix pudding and milk and stir until thick.
Add gummy worms. Crumble Oreo cookies (chocolate wafers only); set aside.
Place pudding and worms in clean clay pot.
Sprinkle Oreo crumbs on top. Place flowers in pot.
Use spade to serve.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix
and
press
into 9 x 13-inch pan 1 stick margarine (melted) and graham cracker crumbs.

title: joe's special
directions: Brown ground beef well in oil in a large frying pan over high heat.
Add onions, garlic and mushrooms.
Reduce heat and continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until onions are soft.
Stir in seasoning and spinach.
Cook about 5 minutes.
Add eggs.
Stir mixture over low heat just until eggs begin to set.
Serve with French bread.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: twice-baked potatoes(low cholesterol)
directions: Slice cabbage fine.
In bowl, combine sugar, vinegar, soy sauce, pepper and salt.
Heat oil in large skillet.
Add garlic and green onions; stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add cabbage and stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir in the sugar-vinegar mixture; heat through and remove from fire.
Serve warm.

title: glazed peach creme
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Dissolve remaining package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add ice cream; stir until smooth and pour into serving bowl.
Chill until set but not firm. Arrange peaches on gelatin/ice cream mixture.
Top with clear gelatin.
Makes 5 cups or 10 servings.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients well and shape into balls.
This is a stiff dough and needs to be mixed with your hands.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Butter pie plate.
Line with buttered tortillas, leaving 1/2-inch extended up.
Sprinkle onion, tomato and chiles in bottom of dish.
Beat eggs.
Mix with flour, salt and baking powder.
Add milk.
Fold in cheese and pour over pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Garnish with sliced avocado, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: saucy chicken
directions: Mix together soup mix, salad dressing and preserves or cranberries.
Pour over chicken and marinate 1 hour in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: nita's brownies
directions: Cream cocoa and shortening together.
Add sugar and then eggs. Mix in flour.
Add nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: pasteli(sesame candy)
directions: Blend sugar and honey in pan.
Add water and cook over low heat, stirring frequently, about 12 minutes, to a soft ball stage. Remove from flame and add sesame seed.
Stir well and spread on buttered pan to 3/4-inch thickness.
When cool, cut into squares, 1 x 2-inch.
Wrap each in waxed paper to keep moist.

title: spiders
directions: Melt white chocolate wafers.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour melted white chocolate over this; mix and toss to coat evenly.
Mound and drop (approximately tablespoon) on waxed paper.
Allow to set until hardened.

title: italian cauliflower
directions: Boil cauliflower, but not too soft.
Dip cauliflower in beaten egg, then bread crumbs mixed with remaining ingredients.
Fry in oil until brown.
Serve with cheese sauce.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli lengthwise.
Halve spears crosswise.
Cook in 1 inch of boiling salted water for 10 to 15 minutes or until just done.
Drain.
Chill broccoli in screw-top jar.
Combine vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil and sugar.
Cover and shake to mix well. Drizzle vinegar mixture over broccoli.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle with toasted sesame seed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: favorite pimiento cheese from bluegrass winners book
directions: Mix well with beater, adding cheese last.
Beat until smooth. Makes 4 cups.

title: peach pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in vanilla.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; add remaining ingredients.
Chill salad about 1 hour before serving.
Will keep up to a week in refrigerator if covered.
Serves 6.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream cheese and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Put through cookie press.
Bake in a slow oven at 325°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large bowl; stir in boiling water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Pour oil to depth of 1/4-inch in large skillet.
Using a tablespoon dipped in hot water; drop cornmeal mixture into hot oil.
Fry over medium heat for 1 minute on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels. Yields 24 fritters.

title: holiday salad
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, whipped cream and pineapple. Cut cherries and marshmallows and add to mixture.
Chill.

title: carne guisada
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic. Sprinkle flour in slowly, stirring constantly.
Add hot water. Add chopped
tomatoes, green chilies and comino seed.	Simmer slowly until
meat
is tender and sauce thickens.	May have to add
small amount
of
hot
water occasionally.
When meat is tender, heat tortillas.	Put meat mixture on tortilla, roll up and serve.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into hot, greased cast-iron skillet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle cheese on top.
Continue baking for 10 to 15 minutes, until done.

title: frosty pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix, pumpkin, milk and spices in bowl. Mix slowly with electric mixer until blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie crust.
Freeze until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before cutting.
Garnish with whipped topping on top.
tags: Jell-O brand vanilla flavor instant pudding

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter.
Put buttered side on bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put aside.

title: wild rice and chicken
directions: *This may be hard to fine, but important.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (approximately 35 to 45 minutes).

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix flour and milk; heat on stove until thick.
Beat egg; add with bread crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and chopped onion to crab meat.
Mix in flour mixture.
Prepare into cakes.
Dip in bread crumbs.
Must be made ahead of time and put in the refrigerator until you are ready to deep fry the cakes.

title: wedding balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix well. Roll by hand into balls. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Place confectioners sugar on wax paper. Remove cookies from oven and roll in sugar. Let cool; roll in sugar two additional times.

title: oriental salad
directions: Toss oranges, bacon and almonds with lettuce and rings of onion.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly. Form into 3 to 6 inch logs and wrap in Saran Wrap. Refrigerate for 24 hours. Place on broiler pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Tear cake into pieces.
Put in a large bowl.
Sprinkle 1/2 of Heath bar bits over cake.
Cook pudding according to package directions and let cool. Pour pudding over cake (mix a bit, if necessary).
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Cover top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with remainder of Heath bar chips.
Kids of all ages love it!

title: sugarless cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add ice cream while hot.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix with fork and put in ungreased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Spread topping on cooled cake.
Keep cake refrigerated.

title: pasta soup
directions: Saute onion in a little oil.
Add carrots and squash.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add garlic and dried seasonings.
Add all cans; simmer 30 minutes.
Add pasta and fresh basil; cook 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan/Romano cheese.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Beat the eggs in a mixing bowl, and add the chicken.
Let marinate in the refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together flour, pecans, margarine and sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: handy shortcake
directions: Mix
all
dry ingredients.
Work in shortening as for pie dough. Add liquids.
If egg is not used, it may take a little more milk.
Bake in 9 x
13-inch
pan or you can cut in half and use smaller pans.
Bake at 375° to 400° until done.
This is delicious with raw or cooked fruit and whole milk.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour 4 x 8 loaf pan. Sift baking powder, baking soda, salt, sugar and flour.
Add cranberries and nuts; mix lightly.
Combine beaten egg, orange juice, melted butter and orange rind.
Combine with flour mixture. Stir just to moisten and fill pan.
Bake 1 hour or until loaf "cake tests" done.
Invert on rack.
Cool 1 hour.

title: icebox lemon pie
directions: In a bowl, mix milk and eggs thoroughly.
Add lemon juice and beat until it starts to thicken.
Pour into pie crust.
In a small bowl, beat reserved egg white and sugar until stiff.
You should be able to form peaks.
Spread over pie.
Brown egg white/sugar mixture in oven.
Refrigerate after it has cooled.

title: cranberry lemonade punch
directions: Make up lemonade concentrate as directed on can.
Pour into punch bowl and stir in cranberry juice.
Add ginger ale and ice cubes.
Mix well.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Makes 48 (4 ounce) servings.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In saucepan, stir together sugar, cocoa and cornstarch.
Add milk.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add almond extract and cool.
Just before serving, stir in Cool Whip.

title: ham and wild rice soup
directions: Rinse and drain wild rice.
Saute in oil until lightly browned; partially cook in water about 30 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid. If necessary, add water to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Over medium heat, saute onion, celery and carrot in butter until onion is transparent; reduce heat.
Blend in flour; cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Cook about 5 minutes but do not brown.
Using wire whisk, blend in chicken broth and reserved wild rice water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add wild rice, half and half and ham; blend well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in rosemary and simmer about 20 minutes; do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.
Yields 10 (1-cup) servings.

title: meg's cheese ball
directions: Melt and stir cheeses.
Add onion and sauces.
Chill until you can mold into a ball.
Mold into a ball and roll into nuts, parsley flakes or celery flakes.

title: pot roast
directions: Put roast in a pot with no handles that can be put in the oven.
Add 1 cup water; pour mushroom soup over roast and add 1 package Lipton onion soup.	Cook for 1 hour per pound at 325°.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Beat together flour, salt, eggs, margarine and sugar.
Soak warm water, sugar, yeast, margarine, brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins 10 minutes or until bubbly.

title: honey blueberry muffins
directions: Stir flour with salt and baking powder.
Combine milk, honey, egg, blueberries and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Stir quickly, just long enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes, or until browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Brown hamburger and onions, then mix all together in baking dish.
Dot with butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook in covered crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours.
With wire whisk or fork, stir until shredded.
Stir occasionally while cooking.

title: chicken `n' rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle uncooked rice in ungreased casserole dish (1 1/2 or 2 qt. size). Mix together in a bowl: 2 cans cream of chicken soup and 1 can water. Pour soup mixture over rice. Stir mixture and rice, making sure all the rice is moistened. Lay raw, salted chicken on top of rice. Cover with lid or foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350 degrees. Remove foil about 30 minutes before serving to brown chicken.

title: potato bacon soup
directions: Spray a 3-quart saucepan with nonstick coating.
Add chopped onions and bacon; cook and stir over medium heat until onions are tender, not brown.
Stir in water and potatoes, bring to boiling and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are just tender.
Using a potato masher, slightly mash some of the potatoes.
Stir in evaporated milk, butter seasoning mix, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.
Do not boil!
Top with sour cream and chives, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: master mix griddle cakes or waffles
directions: Stir the combined milk and beaten egg into the mix until blended.
Bake on hot griddle or in waffle iron.
(Milk can be increased if a thinner griddle cake is desired.
If the batter is thinner, waffles require longer baking to make them crisp.) Yields 6 griddle cakes or 2 waffles.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Place water in a 1-quart measuring cup. Stir in sugar and cornstarch. Microwave on HIGH for 2 to 3 minutes or until boiling. Stir in gelatin until dissolved. Pour over berries in large bowl and toss together gently. Turn into baked pie shell. Chill several hours or until set. May be served with whipped cream or Cool Whip. Serves 6 to 8.

title: lettuce salad
directions: *Take sour cream out a little before using to thin.

title: liquid hand soap
directions: Shred soap using a grater.
Place in a large bowl.
Add water. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until soap is dissolved. Stir every 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Mixture thickens as it cools. Fill pump-type soap dispenser.

title: hurry-up yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix in Bisquick.
Beat vigorously, then turn dough onto surface, well dusted with Bisquick.
Knead until smooth (20 times).
Shape as desired.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Cover with damp cloth.
Let rise in a warm place about 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400° and bake 10 to 15 minutes until brown.
Brush with butter.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in two eight or nine inch cake pans. Cool and cut the 2 layers in half to make 4 layers.
Mix together sugar, sour cream, nuts and coconut.
Spread 1/3 of mixture on each layer of cake (except for top layer). Use frosting mix to frost cake and enjoy.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine ingredients and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Or cook in a crock-pot for a couple of hours.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix well and pour over crushed ice.
Serves 30 to 40.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix dry ingredients and milk.
Add 3 tablespoons of butter to mix.
Pour remaining butter into casserole dish.
Pour batter into dish.
Add berries by mashing in.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine and slightly saute onions.
Place all ingredients in 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in double boiler.
Add pineapple juice and cook 3 minutes.
Cool.
Cream cheese with 2 tablespoons cream.
Add lemon juice, pineapple, oranges, marshmallows, cherries, nuts and mayonnaise to cooled mixture.
Whip 1 cup cream.
Fold into mixture.
Pour into freezing tray.
Freeze until firm. Cut into wedges.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: lemon fruit freeze
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt the margarine and stir in sugar, then add cereal crumbs, reserving 1/3 cup for garnish.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter roll candy
directions: Mix the first five ingredients together.
Roll out to 1/8 to 1/4 inch thick.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill, slice and serve.

title: marinade(great for chicken and spareribs)
directions: Heat all to boiling.
Marinate meat and brush every 15 minutes while cooking.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream sugars, shortening and butter. Add eggs one at a time. Add sifted dry ingredients, alternating with milk. Cook at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swedish bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Cover. Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or microwave for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ramen cabbage salad
directions: Combine Ramen seasoning packets, sugar, vinegar and oil.
Break up Ramen noodles.
Chop cabbage and onions.
Toast almonds and Ramen noodles at 350° for 15 minutes.
Mix together 1/2 hour before serving.

title: hamburger-rice skillet
directions: In skillet, cook beef or pork, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Add rice.
Cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce, basil, 1 1/2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Remove cover, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush 1 roll of cookies at a time.
Separate into 3 bowls. Cream together butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In separate bowl, mix milk, pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix butter mixture and pudding mixture together.
Layer bowl with cookies, pudding, cookies, pudding and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate!

title: lo-cal stuffed mushrooms
directions: Prepare mushrooms; set aside.
Finely chop all peppers and onion.
Mix together with oregano, parsley and water.
Fill each mushroom.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: bandido's(serves 10 people)
directions: Top with sour cream.
Can't beat it.
Wonderful for parties, buffet luncheon or dinners.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: velvet salad
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill at least 2 hours.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: To Hershey's cocoa powder, add butter and melt.
Stir and blend well.
Add boiling water.
Stir well and add sugar, corn syrup and vanilla or rum.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Dip chicken pieces into beaten egg. Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Coat chicken with this dry mixture. Place pieces in 9 x 13 pan. Melt butter and lemon juice in pan. Gently pour 1/2 of this sauce over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Spoon rest of sauce over chicken before serving. Nice served with pasta or rice and a tossed salad.

title: steak marinade
directions: Put meat tenderizer on meat first.
Heat listed ingredients and stir until mixed.
Pour over meat and cover 1 to 2 hours.

title: chip and dip
directions: Mix well; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix and place in round casserole dish. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour, until "firm" and browned.

title: zucchini souffle
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Beat yolks and combine with flour and sour cream.
Fold in egg whites.
Layer in buttered souffle dish:
zucchini, bacon, egg mixture and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 7 minutes.
Pour into an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Pour cherries or pineapple pie filling on top.

title: judith's dip
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Use for vegetables (celery stalks, cauliflower or chips).

title: marbled andes brownies
directions: Preheat oven as indicated on brownie mix.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Brush biscuits with melted butter and sprinkle with sugar. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 14 to 17 minutes or until light golden brown. Split biscuits in half and top with whipped cream and sweetened strawberries.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add shortening and flavoring; beat well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well each time.
Sprinkle nuts with 1 tablespoon flour and stir in.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine ground beef, rice, onion, green pepper, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well to blend.
Shape meat mixture into 24 meatballs, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Place meatballs in slow cooking pot.
Pour soup over meatballs.
Cover and slow cook at setting #3 for 7 to 8 hours, or setting #4 for 4 to 5 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine all-bran cereal, raisins, hot water and oil.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Add to mixture the eggs, buttermilk and molasses. Stir into wet mixture the flour, sugar, baking soda and salt.
Bake at 400° in muffin tins for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: stuffed peppers lorena
directions: Cut tops off peppers and save; remove seeds.
Rinse and drain. In a 10-inch skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Use tops of peppers to dice.
Add onion, rice, diced pepper, bread crumbs, seasoning and butter or margarine.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Fill peppers with mixture.
Place peppers in a glass baking dish.
Pour water in bottom of dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Roast setting for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from microwave, removing plastic wrap.
Cover each pepper with 1/4 slice cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: hot cole slaw
directions: Place vinegar, water, salt, sugar, paprika, mustard and oil in a pan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Combine eggs and cream.
Stir a little of the hot mixture into egg-cream mixture. Continue stirring and slowly pour remaining hot mixture into the egg mixture.
Return to pan and cook on low heat for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix together cabbage, pimiento and pickle relish.
Pour hot dressing over and toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Combine and pour over salad.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix the sugar, Crisco, molasses, eggs and soda mixture together.
Sift the flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt. Add sifted ingredients to cookie dough. Chill dough 1 hour or more. Roll out. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen small or 3 dozen large cookies.

title: italian roast
directions: * We like Kaiser buns.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan, bake the cake. Cool.
Beat cheese, milk and dry pudding mix.
Pour over cake. Chill.
Mix pineapple and topping. Spread on top.
Chill and serve.
Very good!

title: lemon squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place brown sugar and butter in large mixing bowl, beat until light and fluffy. Add flour and lemon rind, beat until well mixed. Mixture should be crumbly. Pat crust into pan. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: broccoli-corn casserole
directions: Reserve several tablespoons of seasoning and about 1 cup stuffing mix.
Thaw broccoli so that it will separate.
Mix vegetables with eggs, slightly beaten, stuffing mix and seasoning. Pour mixture in a buttered casserole dish.
Take reserved crumbs and mix with 1/4 to 1/3 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Add cream cheese and mix with electric beater until cheese is completely dissolved.
Add crushed pineapple and blend well.
Pour into mold or square pan and let set.
Dissolve lemon-lime in 1 cup boiling water.
Add marshmallows and juice and mix with mixer until marshmallows are dissolved.
Add pecans and pour over mixture. Place in refrigerator until set.

title: double crust blueberry pie
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Put in microwave oven on High for about 5 to 6 minutes until hot and changes color. Stir well and mix the vanilla, cinnamon and butter.
Mix all together and pour into a 9 or 10-inch pie plate with unbaked pie crust.
Cover with other crust.
Cut holes in top crust for steam to escape.
Seal edges good or it will leak out.
Cook in a 375° oven until done or golden brown. Cook 45 to 50 minutes depending on oven. Serve warm with ice cream (optional).

title: party salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.
Slice in 1 banana before serving.

title: 24 hour fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons syrup.
To make custard, in small heavy saucepan combine reserved syrup, egg yolks, sugar, vinegar, margarine and salt.
Cook and stir over low heat about 6 minutes or until mixture thickens slightly and coats a metal spoon.
Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple, cherries, oranges and marshmallows.
Pour custard over; mix fruit mixture gently.
Whip the whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Fold whipped cream into fruit mixture. Turn into serving bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.

title: buttermilk tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill 16 tart shells and bake for 40 or 45 minutes or until inserted knife comes out clean.
Very Good!

title: fast food breakfast
directions: Fry sausage; drain well.
Scramble eggs.
Mix sausage and eggs together.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown.

title: cabbage slaw to freeze
directions: Chop cabbage, celery and pepper.
Sprinkle salt over it and let stand until juicy.
Put sugar, vinegar, water and mustard seed in saucepan and bring to a full boil.
Drain vegetables and pour cooled brine over slaw.
Put into containers and freeze.
Will keep for 1 year.
Leftovers can be refrozen.

title: sweet party mix
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Add nuts and cereals and stir.
Use no-stick cooking spray on a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake mix at 325° for seven minutes.
Remove and stir.
Bake an additional seven minutes.
Cool and store in an airtight container.

title: shoe peg corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Ritz crackers and margarine) and place in casserole dish.
Crush crackers and add melted margarine.
Pour over ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 7-layer dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread refried beans.
Sprinkle with sour cream, then picante sauce.
Mash avocados and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Add on top of picante sauce.
Then add diced tomatoes.
Sprinkle top with cheese, then olives.
Chill.

title: raisin-banana tortilla sandwiches
directions: For each sandwich, spread one side of a tortilla with 1/4 cup peanut butter.
Cover with 1/2 banana, sliced; sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons raisins.
Roll tortilla up tightly, jelly-roll fashion; cut in half to serve.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto cookie sheet and bake.
Spread sour cream, mixed with horseradish, salt and pepper, over crust.
When cooled, top with vegetables.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer, do not mix, the next four ingredients in order given.
Pour condensed milk over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares or small bars to serve.
Very rich!

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Blend all ingredients with enough low-fat salad dressing to moisten (about 2 tablespoons of light mayonnaise).
Refrigerate.

title: enchiladas acapulco
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and 1/2 cup peppers. Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beans and 1/4 pound cheese spread; continue cooking until cheese is melted.
Dip tortillas in hot oil; drain.
Fill each tortilla with 1/4 cup meat mixture; roll up.
Place seam side down in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture; cover. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 5 to 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining peppers and tomatoes.

title: celery hot dish
directions: Cook celery 5 minutes in small amount of water; drain.
Add soup, undrained pimento and drained water chestnuts.
Pour into buttered casserole.
May top with buttered bread or cracker crumbs.
Saute slivered almonds and add on top just before serving.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: taco salad dip
directions: Combine sour cream and Philadelphia cream cheese and mix thoroughly with mixer.
Add taco seasoning and stir well.
Spread mixture onto platter; sprinkle finely chopped tomatoes, onions, lettuce and black olives.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: fettuccini souffle(serves 4 to 6)
directions: In a heavy-bottomed saucepan, bring the milk to a boil. Meanwhile, plunge the pasta into rapidly boiling, salted water and cook until al dente, about 7 minutes if dried or 3 minutes if fresh.
Drain the pasta well and mix with the milk, garlic, Parmesan, Gruyere and butter.
Season very generously with salt, pepper and a pinch of nutmeg.
Stir in the herbs (parsley and chervil).
Let the mixture cool for about 5 to 10 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Spread large bowl with lettuce.
Layer onion, celery and drained peas.
Spread mayonnaise over salad layers.
Sprinkle cheese very thick over mayonnaise.
Put crumbled bacon on top. Can put vinegar on peas.
This salad may be made ahead of time. It keeps well and makes several servings.

title: pork tenderloin with pommery-mustard marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pork tenderloin, together.
Let sit for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Next, place pork tenderloin in the marinade and let sit in fridge for 6 to 8 hours. Turn tenderloin and cover with the marinade every hour or so.

title: old-fashioned potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a Dutch oven.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Cook 8 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Place in a large bowl.
Add onion, celery, pickle relish, eggs and garlic.
Toss gently.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, parsley, mustard, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Pour over potato mixture.
Toss to coat. Cover and chill.

title: real southern biscuits
directions: Combine sifted flour, salt, baking powder and soda together. Cut in shortening with pastry blender or knife.
Add buttermilk and mix to make a soft dough.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix zucchini, onions, red and green peppers with salt.
Let sit while mixing remaining ingredients in large kettle.
Cook spices until starts to thicken.
Add zucchini mixture and mix well.
Cook for 20 to 30 minutes stirring often.
Makes 8 pints.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package directions.
Stir butter into hot mixture.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a crust.
In skillet, cook beef, onions and peppers until tender and meat is brown.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Put mixture into crust.
Bake, uncovered, at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put into dish. Place in refrigerator until cold.

title: never fail chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together to mix well.
Add milk, oil and eggs; blend together with a big spoon.
Add water and vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.
This is a thin batter and makes a moist cake.

title: shrimp dip
directions: In blender, beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually blend in soup until smooth. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: southern slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, carrot, onion and salad oil.
Toss until cabbage is coated.
Chill.
Mix remaining ingredients; combine with cabbage mixture.
Serve cold.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt; add water and let set for 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: cheese garlic bread
directions: Combine all ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Drop dough by heaping tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450° until golden brown.
Combine 1/4 cup melted margarine and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Brush over hot biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 12 to 15 biscuits.

title: nebraska pumpkin pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, eggs, melted butter and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Bake in deep dish or large pie pan with unbaked pie crust at 450° for 15 minutes and continue baking at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna and broccoli bake
directions: Place broccoli on bottom of 2-quart baking dish.
Top with bread cubes and tuna.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, cottage cheese, Cheddar cheese and pepper.
Spread evenly over tuna mixture.
Bake in 400° oven 30 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.

title: waffle iron cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar and butter. Add the eggs.
Sift together flour, salt and cinnamon. Blend in creamed mixture. Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Drop teaspoonfuls onto hot waffle iron. Bake with top down for about 1 1/2 minutes.
If you wish, frost with your favorite chocolate frosting. Store in airtight container to keep soft and fresh.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Prepare evening before.
Cook sausage and drain thoroughly on paper towels.
Beat eggs and milk slightly.
Add sausage, cubed bread and cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch casserole and cover. Refrigerate overnight.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Shape loaf and bake in greased pan for 1 hour, draining off excess fat.
Baste with barbecue sauce mixed with a little water at 350°.

title: grandma's banana bread
directions: Put all ingredients in large bowl at once.
Mix well by hand or electric mixer.
Put in greased loaf pans.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 1 1/4 hours.
Let cool in pans about 15 minutes. Finish cooling on wire racks.
These freeze very well.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Stir in milk, butter and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread batter into ungreased 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Stir together remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes, spooning sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Garnish with whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: crazy crust pizza
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and pour on greased and floured pizza pan.
On top of mixture, add hamburger and onion. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then add pizza sauce, cheese and other toppings.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: venison summer sausage
directions: Grind together pork and venison.
Add Tender Quick, smoke salt, pepper, liquid smoke and mustard seed.

title: spicy sausage balls
directions: Roll
sausage
into
balls
about
the	size of pecans. Broil in oven about 10 minutes.
Turn while broiling.
Drain. Mix
sauce in pan and heat until bubbly.
Add sausage balls to sauce.	Serve in chafing dish to keep hot.
Yummy but easy!

title: refrigerator pickles
