directions: Wash and slice 1/2 of cucumbers in large mouth gallon jar. Slice onion and put on top of cucumbers. Slice remainder of cucumbers and add. Mix all other ingredients. Stir well and add to cucumber and onion (DO NOT HEAT!). Cover and keep in the refrigerator. Good after 5 days, but are better the longer you wait. Will last up to 1 year in the refrigerator.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cook oleo and brown sugar into a syrup slowly.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook in 9 x 14-inch pan in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: cowboy delight
directions: In a skillet, brown the first 4 ingredients.
Drain off all grease.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; heat.
Layer in greased casserole half of the cooked macaroni, half of the meat mixture, the corn and half of the cheese.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together until very smooth.
Shape into 2 long rolls, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Combine parsley or chives with nuts.
Roll the cheese in mixture and chill until fairly firm.
Serve in slices with crisp unsalted crackers. (Freezes well.)

title: oven baked chicken paprikash
directions: Sprinkle chicken heavy with paprika, lightly with salt and cayenne pepper.
Place in roaster; spread onions on top.
Add bay leaves.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir chicken once during this 45 minutes.
When chicken is browned, add enough water to just cover the chicken. Stir chicken so the paprika is blended into water.
Return to oven to blend flavors, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend together sour cream and flour and slowly add broth from chicken.
When blended, slowly add broth in roaster.
Stir to thicken for 15 minutes.
Serve with noodles.

title: barbecued ribs(my son, dan, can't get enough of this recipe.)
directions: In a saucepan, parboil ribs until tender.
Place in casserole dish.
In a bowl, mix remaining ingredients, then pour on top of ribs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix listed ingredients and store in airtight container.
(I add peanut butter chips.)

title: lonnie's apple crumb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush pie crust with egg white.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Spoon pie filling into crust. In a small bowl, mix flour, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle evenly over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cool slightly on wire rack.
(Sprinkle top with powdered sugar, if desired.)
Garnish with apple slices and mint sprigs.
Makes 7 servings.
Preparation time:

title: hamburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients into hamburger meat, form into patties and cook.

title: chicken-broccoli divan
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a 10 x 6-inch pan arrange broccoli and chicken.
In mixing bowl, combine soup and milk.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
In bowl, combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top and bake 15 minutes or until hot.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Grease baking dish.
Mix oleo with stuffing mix (add flavor packet).
Put half of stuffing mixture in bottom of baking dish. Mix squash, onion, soup and sour cream together.
Put on top of stuffing mixture, then add rest of stuffing mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: baked pizza spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add onion, tomato paste, water, mushrooms and oregano.
Cook vermicelli; drain and toss with melted butter.
Combine vermicelli, meat mixture and the Cheddar cheese.
Stir well until blended.
Pour into 2 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: party dawgs
directions: Mix chili sauce and grape jelly.
Pour in saucepan or crock-pot.
Add cocktail sausages.
Heat until jelly melts and "dawgs" are hot.

title: golden apples and chicken hawaiian
directions: Saute apples, green pepper, garlic and curry powder in margarine until tender.
Add soup, chicken and pineapple with liquid to skillet.
Heat through.
Serve over rice; garnish with almonds.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: hobo bread
directions: Soak raisins in boiling water.
Add soda. Stir and cover.
Let stand overnight. In the morning, add sugar, salt and oil. Add flour, one cup at a time, stirring well after each cup.
Grease and flour 3 (1 pound) coffee cans or 2 loaf pans. Fill half full. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes, then shake out of can or remove from pans.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the butter and peanut butter.
Add sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients.
Form into balls the size of walnuts and place on greased pan. Flatten with floured fork, making crisscross patterns.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 375° oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: sweet and sour swedish meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and shape.
Roll meatballs, then bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Freeze
if
desired.
To serve, combine 1 jar French's mustard and	1
jar currant jelly.
Heat and pour over meatballs.
Serve warm.

title: stuffed crust pepperoni pizza
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease or spray 13 x 9-inch pan.
Unroll dough and press in bottom and 1-inch up sides of greased pan. Place pieces of string cheese along inside edges of dough.
Fold 1-inch of dough over and around cheese; press dough edges to seal. Top crust with pizza sauce, pepperoni and shredded cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 18 minutes or until crust is golden brown and cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: k c's chicken salad
directions: Dissolve the Knox gelatine in water and then melt over boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Place in oblong Pyrex dish and chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grape bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 bread pans and flour; cream sugar, eggs, oil and spices.
Add remaining ingredients, except grape skins.
Mix well; fold in grape skins.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: sausage potatoes
directions: Take the sausage and make big balls out of them.
You will make about 4 or 5 balls of sausage out of 1 pound.
Put sausage balls in a big bread pan and the potatoes in bread pan, too.
Cover with water.
Bake in oven about 2 hours.
Put tinfoil over pan to bake.

title: chocochip marshmallow pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, milk and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, just until marshmallows are melted. Chill until partially set.
In chilled bowl, beat cream until stiff; fold in marshmallow mixture, vanilla and chocolate.
Pile into the pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours or until set.

title: variety baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° in oven or in crock-pot on low for 4 to 5 hours.
To stretch for a bigger group, add an additional small can of pork and beans.

title: dietabic strawberry pie
directions: Cook on stove until clear. Stir in 1 envelope NutraSweet strawberry jello and 1 pint strawberries. Pour into prebaked pie shell. Top with 1/2 package Deserta topping.

title: spinach bread
directions: Saute chopped onion in butter; add Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese until melted.
Add 1 box of boiled, chopped spinach to cheese mixture.
Quickly spread on French bread.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix as given (milk, pineapple, cherry pie filling, nuts and Cool Whip).
Freeze in square 9 x 9-inch pan or dish.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: turtle bars
directions: Melt caramels with milk in double boiler or over low heat.
Mix by hand the cake mix, margarine and nuts until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 dough into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes at 350° (preheated oven).
Remove from oven and spread semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Pour on caramel mixture. Crumble remaining dough over caramel mixture.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate to set caramel.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together.
Stir in milk, oil and nuts.
Spread mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend in small bowl the brown sugar and cocoa.
Sprinkle over top of batter.
Pour over all 3 cups hot water.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: pineapple fruit dessert
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Substitute pineapple juice from pineapple in place of water (if not enough juice, add water to make up the difference).
When cake is cool, cover top with 2 cans vanilla pudding, then spread pineapple on top of pudding.
Then spread Cool Whip on top.
Chill in refrigerator.
Makes a delicious cool dessert and it's easy!!!

title: blueberry swirl cheesecake
directions: Mix together, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Add eggs, mix will.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Spoon about 1/3 of pie filling on top.
Gently swirl with wooden pick.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out one pie crust shell.
Break Ritz crackers coarsely into pastry lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Boil gently for 15 minutes (low heat).
Add lemon juice and let cool.
(Mixture turns into syrup.)
Pour syrup over crackers; dot generously with butter or margarine, then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges together.
Cut slits into top crust to let steam escape.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
Serve warm.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt oleo and pour over brown sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except parsley and use only 2 teaspoons of cocktail sauce; add rest of cocktail sauce on top.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve with crackers or vegetables.

title: toll house chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to
325°.	Beat
eggs until foamy; beat in flour, sugar and
brown
sugar
until
well blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. May be served warm
with
whipped cream or ice cream.
Pie can be frozen for later use.

title: seven bean salad
directions: Cook the frozen beans and drain.
Rinse all the canned and jarred beans thoroughly.

title: macaroni and chickpeas
directions: Boil the 2 cups of elbow macaroni.
Follow directions on the box.
Saute the 2 medium onions in the 2 tablespoons of oil.
Open the can of chickpeas and slowly add to the onions (juice also). Drain the macaroni and add the chickpea and onion mixture.
Use salt and pepper to add spice.
Eat and enjoy.
This is a family recipe passed down from my grandmother.

title: taco casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add chopped onion and pepper until tender.
Add tomatoes and seasoning and let cook about 10 minutes.
Layer Tostitos, corn and then beef mixture.
Put grated cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy tartar sauce
directions: Mix salad dressing and relish together until well blended, then refrigerate.

title: oreo delight
directions: Combine milk with pudding and blend until smooth.
Mix sugar and cream cheese together.
Combine pudding, whipped cream and cream cheese all together.
Crumble Oreo cookies.
Layer cookies, then cream cheese mixture in dish.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix ingredients in food processor and pour into 8-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy party rolls
directions: Place rolls in freezer 30 minutes to one hour ahead of time. Slice entire package of rolls horizontally.
Place ham on bottom section of rolls.
Top with cheese.
Replace roll tops.
Melt butter; add other ingredients and stir.
Pour over rolls (pull out sides of pan). Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes or until thoroughly heated and cheese melts.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar together.
Then add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after adding each one until smooth.
Add flour and soda alternately with buttermilk.
Then add coconut and pecans.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: In a shallow glass bowl, combine orange juice and cornstarch; mix well. Stir in chicken. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 2 hours. Drain chicken; discard juice mixture.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Stir together the first 3 ingredients.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Put on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. This is like an upside-down cake.

title: pluckett(sweet rolls)
directions: Mix and cool ingredients to lukewarm.
Crumble 2 cakes of yeast into the mixture.
Add 2 beaten eggs and 4 1/2 cups flour. Mix to a soft dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and cover with damp cloth.
Let rise until double (about 2 hours).
Punch down and let stand 10 minutes.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain and save shrimp liquid.
Cut up Crab Delights as desired.
Combine pasta, shrimp, crab, celery, pepper and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dill weed.
Thin with some shrimp liquid.
Mix as needed with other ingredients.

title: greek style cabbage
directions: Cut head of cabbage
in
6 sections.
Cover with water; bring to boil, then
simmer
for	40
minutes.
Place
cooked cabbage on platter.
Pour
olive
oil over cabbage and arrange lemon wedges around the cabbage.
Serve as a side dish or as a vegetable.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter together.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: india relish
directions: Remove seed from peppers.
Put peppers, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion through food chopper, using coarse blade.
Stir salt into vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, place vegetables in a colander and force out as much brine as possible. Chop cabbage very fine.
Combine all the vegetables.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices.
Mix well and heat to boiling.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pack into sterilized jars to within 1/2-inch of top. Put on cap.
Screw band firmly tight.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yield:
8 pints.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Prepare eggs, cool.
Slice oblong.
Remove yolks and place in bowl.
Mash with fork.
Add salt, relish and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Spoon back into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: salad dressing
directions: Add together and blend.
Be sure to add curry powder.

title: heavenly hash]
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Cool Whip.
Once mixed, then add Cool Whip.
Cover and let set in refrigerator before serving.

title: german pickles
directions: Place pickles, 1 gallon cold water and salt in a churn.
Let stand 8 days in this saltwater.

title: boiled cookies("bunny nests")
directions: Boil butter, sugar, milk and cocoa for 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter, salt, vanilla and coconut.
Shape as desired.
Put jelly beans in nests to represent bunny eggs.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, cheese, beef or ham (chopped up), Worcestershire and onion salt.
Form ball and roll in pecans to cover.
Keep chilled.
Serve with crackers.

title: "my favorite" cheese balls
directions: Mix all with 1/2 cup pecans.
Form 2 balls and roll in chopped pecans.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Sprinkle nuts over crumbs.
Scatter chips.
Sprinkle coconut.
Pour on condensed milk.
Bake until lightly browned at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan 15 minutes. Cut into bars.

title: peach custard pie
directions: Place halves of fresh peaches on 9-inch unbaked pie shell, cut side up.
Beat egg slightly; add sugar and flour.
If you like cinnamon or nutmeg, add a sprinkle.
Pour peaches.
Bake at 375° until custard is set.

title: mock kahlua
directions: Combine coffee, sugar and water. Cool. Add vodka and vanilla bean.
Pour into glass jug or bottle. Age for 30 days.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Layer sausage, bread and cheese in casserole in two layers. Beat together eggs, milk and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Put in cold oven at 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: corey's olive salad
directions: Dissolve both packages of jello in hot water. Soften cream cheese and mix into the Cool Whip. When jello has cooled, mix the cream cheese-Cool Whip mixture into the jello. Add some chopped salad olives and crushed pineapple and pour into a salad mold. Refrigerate.

title: frozen cranberry sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze.
Serve frozen and refreeze.
Freeze leftovers.

title: cole slaw
directions: Add any other vegetables to your liking.

title: grilled marinated turkey steaks
directions: Purchase bone-in turkey breast. Have it cut in half lengthwise, then cut each half crosswise into 1-inch thick "steaks" resembling large pork chops. Combine soy sauce and remaining ingredients; pour over turkey. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours. Remove turkey from marinade. Grill turkey, covered with lid, over medium hot coals (358° to 400°) for 8 to 10 minutes on each side. Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper and pound them until thin (about 1/4-inch).
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika in plastic bag.
Add chicken breasts and coat well.
Shake off excess.
Heat butter and olive oil in large skillet until bubbling.
Saute chicken, a few at a time, 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Do not overcook.
Drain on paper towels and keep warm. Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of butter and oil.
Stir Madeira or water into drippings, scraping bottom of skillet to loosen any browned bits.
Add lemon juice and heat briefly.
Return chicken to skillet, interspersing with lemon slices.
Heat until sauce thickens.
Add capers.
Sprinkle with minced parsley.

title: orange salad
directions: Add 2 cups hot water to jello.
Fold in the orange juice (undiluted).
Add mandarin oranges (drained) and the pineapple (not drained).
Let jell in the refrigerator.
Fix lemon pudding with one cup milk and let firm up.
Blend in the Cool Whip and spread on top of the jello.
Serve.

title: hamburger sauce casserole
directions: Add ketchup, onion mix, onion and enough water to make consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Brown hamburger.
Combine hamburger and ketchup to cooked macaroni. Place all ingredients in a greased casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted, then serve.

title: quick liver pate
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Pat firmly into mold.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Unmold and ice with softened cream cheese.

title: diabetic chili
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Cook for 1 hour.
Or cook in slow cooker on low for 10 to 12 hours; or on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: marinated broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli flowerets into bite size pieces and wash thoroughly.
Drain well.
Add onion, raisins and bacon.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, sugar and vinegar.
Toss the 2 mixtures and refrigerate for at least 3 hours.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and add shrimp in last.
Best served with Club crackers.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Boil together 5 minutes the brown sugar, salt, tomato paste and water.
Melt oleo and pour over bread, then pour over tomato sauce.
Lift bread carefully with table knife to make sure bread is covered with sauce.
Bake, uncovered,
at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lenna's lemon fluff
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and let congeal to thick consistency, but not firm.
Fold in evaporated milk, chilled and whipped.
Roll into fine crumbs vanilla wafers or coconut macaroons.
Place half of the crumbs in the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(I use Pyrex.)
Pour in the fluff.
Spread evenly and cover with remaining half of crumbs.
Place in refrigerator until firm. Serves 12.
Delicious!

title: grandma shirley's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 7 ingredients; stir to evenly distribute and add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into large casserole.
Crush saltine crackers and spread over mixture. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until crackers are golden brown.

title: punch for 75 people
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients. Add the ginger ale and sherbet when ready to serve.

title: citrus fruit slush
directions: Boil 6 cups water and sugar until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
To use add 1 quart Ginger Ale to each 1/2 gallon frozen slush.
Break up with fork.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Spread each muffin half with a tablespoon of soup.
Sprinkle with oregano and cheese.
Place 4 muffin halves in a paper towel lined 1 1/2-quart oblong glass baking dish.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until hot, turning dish once.
Makes 16 individual pizzas.

title: favorite tea
directions: In large pot, pour boiling water over other ingredients and let steep ten minutes. Remove mint and tea bags, serve over ice. Garnish with fresh mint, lemon wedge or orange slice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all preceding well and place in baking dish.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Scald milk.
Beat 2 egg yolks.
Add 2 tablespoons scalded milk to yolks.
Mix well.
Add yolk to rest of scalded mix.
Cook until it coats a metal spoon.
Dissolve gelatine in cold water.
Add gelatine to milk.
Add 2 1/2 tablespoons sugar, salt and vanilla to milk.
Stir until well mixed.
Remove from heat.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat egg whites until stiff, gradually adding 3 tablespoons sugar.
Fold egg whites to cooled yolk mixture.
Pour in crust.
Sprinkle with chopped chips.
Refrigerate.
When served, top with whipped cream.

title: beachcomber casserole
directions: Cook shell macaroni according to directions; drain.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper in lard or drippings.
Combine meat mixture, salt, pepper, macaroni, corn, tomato soup and ripe olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and combine with 1/4 cup margarine and next 6 ingredients.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with cornflakes or stuffing and drizzle 1/2 cup melted margarine over the top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hot spiced tea
directions: Combine ingredients and store in tightly covered jar.
Makes 24 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, soup, onion, salt, mayonnaise, almonds, lemon juice, eggs, celery and pimento in a large bowl.
Place in greased baking dish. Cover with potato chips or crackers. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Sliced water chestnuts may be used instead of almonds.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients; add muffin mix last (just before baking). Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pat hamburger into bottom of cake pan. Sprinkle salt, pepper and onion over hamburger.
Arrange frozen French fries in layer over hamburger.
Spread soups over French fries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Break cake into pieces and line 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions and add cream cheese mixture; mix well.
Spread over cake.
Top with strawberries and glaze; keep in refrigerator.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil whole zucchini in boiling, salted water for 15 minutes, until barely tender.
Drain, trim ends and cut lengthwise in halves.
Carefully scoop out the pulp.
Arrange shells in a greased shallow baking dish.

Mash the scooped out pulp; add the eggs, crumbs, cheese, butter, onion, parsley, seasonings and garlic; mix well. Fill zucchini shells with the pulp mixture. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in egg.
Sift all remaining ingredients, then add to other mixture.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours so it will be easy to handle. Roll dough over part at a time to 1/8-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Transfer to cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot dill pickle
directions: Bring to a boil water, vinegar and salt.
Put pickles in jars (whole or sliced).
Add garlic, pepper, alum and dill.
Pour over pickles in jar and seal.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix
Veg-All
and
chestnuts
together, drain.	Mix all together and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 roll crushed Ritz crackers
over this.
Drizzle 2 or 3 tablespoons melted margarine over
top.	Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until real bubbly.

title: sweet and sour franks
directions: Cut wieners in 1 inch lengths. In a saucepan, mix all ingredients. Bring to boil. Add wieners and simmer, covered, for about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve with cocktail picks.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Beat together Cheddar cheese and cream cheese.
Beat in deviled ham.
Stir in chopped olives.
Chill and shape into ball or two 8-inch long logs.
Roll in 1/2 cup finely chopped pecans or walnuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy crumb cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions in pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch.
Mix the rest of ingredients, until crumbly, with hands. Distribute as evenly as possible on top of cooled cake.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into 4 patties. Chill between sheets of wax paper for 30 minutes before frying or grilling. Salt and pepper, if desired.

title: peach ice cream
directions: To peaches, add sugar and 1/4 cup water; mash.
Add 1 to 2 drops each red and yellow food coloring.
Drain reserved juice. Add water to juice and milk; pour into refrigerator trays.
Freeze until firm.
Break into chunks.
Beat fluffy with electric mixer. Fold in whipped cream and nuts.
Return to trays.
Freeze firm. Serves 8 to 10.

title: bavarian style sauerkraut
directions: Rinse kraut with warm water; drain well.
Cook onion and bacon in butter until onion is soft.
Add kraut, caraway seed, sugar and bouillon and cover tightly.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Add sausage or other meat.
Cook another 1/2 hour or more.
Kraut is especially good if made one day and reheated at a later date.

title: spinach superb
directions: Cook spinach; drain.
Mix all.
Pour in a greased casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple rice pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add to cooked rice and stir in salt, sugar, milk and pineapple.
Mix.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: zucchini and tomatoes
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil, cook onion, green pepper and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add tomatoes with liquid and next 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until zucchini are tender-crisp, about 15 minutes, stirring occasionally to break up tomatoes.
When zucchini are done, sprinkle evenly with cheese. Cover and simmer for about 3 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Preheat the chocolate brownie layer. Coat a 9 inch cake pan with 1 tsp of butter. Flour the pan with 1 tsp of flour, shake out the excess.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat. Add soda to buttermilk, then add to butter and sugar. Place flour in bowl.
Add dates, orange slices and nuts.
Stir to coat.
Add flour mixture and coconut.
Place in greased and floured pan. Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients; stir well.
Pour over chicken until all is covered.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate zucchini
directions: In a medium bowl, mix together flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, beat together sugar and margarine.
Beat in applesauce, eggs and vanilla until thoroughly blended.
Gradually add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Stir in zucchini.
Pour into a greased 9-cup Bundt pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool slightly and dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind all together coarsely.
Mix and cook until thick.
Seal while hot.

title: recipe for a happy marriage
directions: May all the joys and pleasures that make a happy life, be yours in fullest measure, to share as man and wife.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together; spoon over chicken. Bake 45 minutes at 375°, uncovered.

title: homemade egg noodles
directions: Measure flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Make well in center; add eggs and oil.
Stir with fork until flour is moistened, adding water if necessary.
Press into a ball.
On lightly floured surface, knead dough about 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic. Wrap in plastic wrap; chill 1 hour.
Divide into quarters.
Roll each out into 1/16-inch thick strips, 4 inches wide and as long as possible.
Let dry while you roll out remaining dough.
Roll up lengthwise and cut into slices.
Unroll and drape over drying rack to dry 30 minutes before cooking.
Cook in boiling salted water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain and serve with sauce of your choice.

title: pink beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Next day, add ham or bacon, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook until done (about 2 hours), adding more water if beans become dry.
Keep beans barely covered with water while cooking.
After beans are done, add tomato paste and if necessary, more salt.

title: creole eggplant*
directions: Peel and slice eggplants.
Place in pot in salt water for 1 hour, then cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add egg, tomato, salt, cheese, onion and pepper to eggplant.
Stir in baking powder and bacon drippings.
Combine and place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake for 40 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes 8 servings.

title: pepper jelly cheese ball
directions: Blend above ingredients. Chill. When firm, mold into ball. Roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: italian pasta stir-fry
directions: Cook linguine as directed on package. Heat olive oil in large skillet. Add garlic, zucchini and onions. Stir-fry 3 to 5 minutes until crisp-tender. Add tomatoes, parsley and seasonings. Heat 2 more minutes; remove. Stir in cooked linguine. Top with grated Parmesan cheese. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in quarters.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Roll quartered biscuits in cinnamon/sugar mixture.
Place cut biscuits in greased tube or Bundt pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over very low heat.
Add peanuts and salt; allow to warm.
Place sugar in large thick skillet over medium heat.
Stir continuously until sugar caramelizes into golden brown syrup.
Stir peanuts into syrup quickly.
Pour onto large buttered surface at once.
With big spoon, stretch and pull candy into thin sheet.
Cool and break into pieces.
Yields 1 1/2 pounds brittle.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Mix all other ingredients together in saucepan over low heat.
Drain beef and mix together. Heat through and serve.

title: microwave oven fudge
directions: Lightly grease an 8-inch square pan.
Add confectioners sugar to cocoa in a microwave-safe bowl. Add milk and butter.
Do not stir.
Heat, uncovered, at full power for 2 minutes.
After cooking, stir just enough to combine ingredients. Add vanilla and nuts. Stir to blend.
Pour into pan. Refrigerate 1 hour before cutting.

title: georgia pecan pie
directions: Combine eggs and corn syrup; mix well.
Add sugar; mix thoroughly.
Stir in salt and vanilla.
Let stand 5 minutes. Spread pecans on bottom of pie shell.
Stir melted margarine into syrup mixture, then pour over pecans.
Be sure all pecans rise to the top.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 375°. or until center is firm.

title: marie's carrot cake
directions: Cream all ingredients, spread on cooled cake.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs, vanilla, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 5 to 10 minutes.

title: bourbon cake
directions: Grate chocolate chips or bar and set aside.
Mix raisers and nuts with 1/4 cup flour so they are completely coated and set aside.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form and set aside. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.

Sift together 2 cups flour, baking powder and salt, then add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and bourbon, beating well between additions. Fold in egg whites, then grated chocolate, nuts and raisins. (Reserve some chocolate mixture for garnish.)
Pour into 2 well greased and floured pans and bake for 25 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
Cool on rack and frost.

title: pasta salad
directions: Measure sugar out and add the garlic powder, celery seed and black pepper.
Then gradually add the vinegar.
Last, add the vegetable oil and pour over the pasta and vegetables.
Let stand for 2 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In skillet, in hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and thyme.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 35 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: steak soup
directions: Melt oleo and whip flour in to make a smooth paste.
Stir in water.
Saute ground beef; drain off grease.
Add to soup.
Add onions, celery and carrots which have been boiled.
Add frozen vegetables, tomatoes, Accent, beef base and black pepper.
Boil, reduce, simmer and cook until vegetables are done.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup
of
cheese and 1/2 cup of French fried onions.
Place in
8 x
12-inch	baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Cook in Bundt pan.
Start in cold oven at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Glaze with powdered sugar glaze.
Mix enough warm water with 1 cup powdered sugar to pour over cake.

title: leg of lamb mosaic
directions: Position rack in center of oven and preheat to 325°.
Pat meat dry.
Place on surface, fell side down with long edge toward you. Sprinkle with rosemary and garlic.
Cover with layer of spinach leaves.
Arrange 4 carrots in 2 rows across center of meat. Surround carrots with pimientos.
Scatter onion slices atop carrots.
Sprinkle with parsley, 2 teaspoons salt, 3/4 teaspoon pepper and cayenne.
Starting at short end, roll meat up tightly. Tie securely with kitchen twine at 2-inch intervals.
Place on rack in roasting pan.
Add celery, 2 chopped carrots and onion to pan.
Pour vermouth over meat.

Season with salt and pepper. Roast until thermometer inserted in thickest part of meat registers 130° (for medium rare), about 1 1/2 hours, adding up to 1/2 cup water to pan if necessary to keep vegetables from sticking.
Transfer meat to cutting board; let stand 15 minutes.

title: lemon berry charlotte
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Mix cold water and ice to make 1 3/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until ice is melted.
Refrigerate 10 minutes or until slightly thickened, if necessary.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups of the whipped topping and strawberries.
Spoon into 2-quart saucepan (about 3 1/2 inches deep) which has been lined with plastic wrap. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Invert saucepan onto serving plate; remove plastic wrap.
Spread top and sides of dessert with 1 cup of the whipped topping.
Press cut sides of ladyfingers into sides of dessert. Tie ribbon around dessert. Garnish with remaining whipped topping, strawberry halves and mint leaves. Store leftover dessert in refrigerator.
Makes 12 servings.

title: southwestern style meat or fajitas
directions: Put meat of your choice in crock-pot.
Pour salsa over it. Cook all day on low, or half day on high.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken and save 1 1/2 cups of the broth.
Debone the chicken and place in the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan. Mix together 1 1/2 cups of broth with the soup and pour evenly over the chicken.
Mix together Bisquick and milk; pour evenly over all.
Top with butter and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: candy trifles
directions: In top of double boiler, over hot water, melt chocolate pieces. Stir in nuts and noodles until well coated. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until firm.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients. Add 1 cup of apples to oil mixture and beat.
Add flour mixture. Fold in remaining apples, vanilla and nuts.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco casserole
directions: Crush up Doritos; put in bottom of medium size casserole dish. Brown ground beef in skillet.
Combine cream of mushroom soup and taco seasoning mix.
Add a little water; pour into meat mixture. Blend well, then pour meat mixture over crushed chips.
Cover with sharp shredded cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread.
Arrange bread in 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with chicken, then cover with mushrooms and water chestnuts. Beat eggs; blend in milk, mayo and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pimento and pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy broccoli soup
directions: Saute butter and onion. Add flour to make white base. Add other ingredients and simmer till thick.

title: spinach dill dip
directions: Mix together.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cool in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours.

title: pinto bean pie(like pecan pie)
directions: Mix ingredients together with an electric mixer.
After mixture has been mixed together, spoon in 1 cup coconut.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: passover macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Gradually beat in sugar and flour; fold in coconut.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet; bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's bean soup
directions: Soak beans overnight, then drain.
Cook everything except carrots and potatoes.
After bringing to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for about 3 hours.
Put carrots and potatoes in about 1 hour before beans are done.
Remove meat from bones and return to soup. Think of me and enjoy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: vegetable corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients, add milk if needed.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Bake in 10 inch iron skillet till done, using toothpick method.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break cake layers into pieces; put half of cake in bottom of punch bowl or trifle container.
Spread half of pudding on top, half of blueberry filling next, then cherry pie filling.
Add layer of half of pineapple; top with half of the Cool Whip, then nuts.
Repeat the layers.
Chill well.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Add vinegar and sugar to tomatoes and process in blender.
Cook carrots, celery and potatoes and bouillon in 2 cups water for 5 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook in 1 pot for about 1 hour.
May add 2-3 Tbsp. parsley if desired.
May substitute ground turkey for beef.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add taco seasoning, tomato soup and 1/2 cup water.
Oil bottom of a cookie sheet.
Place 2 shells on sheet.
Top with beans, then 2 more shells.
Put beef mix on, then Monterey Jack cheese.
Top with 2 more shells.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake as directed in two 9 x 13-inch or one 12 x 16-inch cake pans.

title: mashed potatoes for a crowd
directions: Peel, cut up and boil the potatoes (salt to taste) until done; drain water. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix with electric mixer until well blended. Pour into casserole dish (sprayed with nonstick cooking spray). Bake in 300° oven until potatoes rise and are very lightly browned.

title: sausage breakfast biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare biscuits as directed on package. Cut biscuits in half.
Brown sausage as directed on package.

title: comfort cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1
hour.
Set on racks to cool. Invert
on
platter
or cake
plate.
Pierce
top
and drizzle my favorite glaze on top.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage, apple, water and salt over low heat for 15 minutes.
Mix flour and vinegar until smooth.
Add to cabbage mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 15 minutes longer. Serves 6.

title: sour cream molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate dough until semi-stiff. Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute before removing from pan.
Makes 8 to 10 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat egg; add corn, milk, honey and salt and pepper.
Add all but a small amount of cracker crumbs and blend well.
Place in a well-buttered casserole (approximately 6 x 10-inches) and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: new potato salad
directions: Mix all together and serve at once.

title: killer meat loaf
directions: Heat butter, add veggies and garlic, cook until veggies dry up.
Let cool and chill.
Combine spices, eggs, ketchup, half and half, blend.
Mix veggie mix, spice mix, meats and crumbs all together.
Blend well.
Shape into loaf, put in pan, then put pan into a slightly larger pan with some water.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, then melt 1 stick butter in pan. Soak chicken in butter, roll and press each piece of chicken in combined mixture.
Place back in shallow long pan.
Pour remaining butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 400°.
Good served with lasagna or spaghetti.

title: herb taters
directions: Peel or scrub potatoes.
Slice each potato diagonally into thin slices down to about 1/2-inch of the bottom.
Use a knife, laying alongside your potato to stop your cut from going all the way through your potato.
Put into baking dish; open slices slightly. Drizzle with butter; sprinkle with seasonings.
Bake at 425° for about 40 minutes.
Remove.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Before serving, put bacon bits and green onions.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil; beat well.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Mix cocoa and red coloring.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Add eggs, beating hard after each.
Add flour mixture, milk and vanilla to beater.
Beat until blended.
Pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dorito pie
directions: Brown meat in large skillet. Drain. Add soup, sauce and milk. In a 9 x 13 inch pan, layer meat mixture, then chips until through. End with meat mixture. Top with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with tossed salad.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Wrap bacon and beef
around
each
piece of chicken and place in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chicken. Bake 3 hours at 275°.
Serve over rice.

title: noodle candy
directions: Melt chips over a double boiler or in a microwave; then add noodles and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: corn pudding vegetable
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Easy.
Delicious.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix in glass or plastic container; cover and put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Shape into 4 rolls and bake at 250° for 2 hours, then turn them over and bake for 2 more hours.
Bake on a broiler pan.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour 1/2 batter into warm greased skillet.
Spread rest of ingredients
over this and add remaining batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 400°.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Put everything together in a can or something to store in.
Mix well.
When ready to use, add 2 tablespoons per mug and add hot water.

title: rice medley
directions: Fry sausage until brown; drain well.
Place meat and chopped vegetables in 3-quart baking dish.
Add rice, broth and mushrooms; mix well.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, or until liquid is completely absorbed.
Stir occasionally.

title: chili
directions: Mix together.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add 2 tablespoons chili powder.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients, except cookies, for 2 minutes.
Add coarsely chopped cookies to mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack. Frost with Cool Whip.
Garnish with cookies (as you wish).

title: chicken in mushroom gravy
directions: Place chicken pieces in slow cooker or crock-pot.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Add mushrooms.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours (or high 3 to 4 hours).

title: brown bag apple pie
directions: Put sliced apples in pie shell.
Combine 1 cup sugar, salt, cinnamon and 5 tablespoons of flour.
Sprinkle flour/sugar mixture over the apples.
Sprinkle 3 tablespoons water over flour/sugar mixture on the apples.
Combine margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup flour in a bowl.
Sprinkle mixture over pie.
Wet a brown paper bag on the outside and place pie inside the bag.
Bake 1 hour at 425°.

title: shrimp and noodle casserole
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, excluding the chow mein noodles.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Top with chow mein noodles if desired and bake 10 more minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Mix rest of ingredients and bake in moderate oven until done.

title: no bake trick or treat
directions: Grease an 8-inch square baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine cereal and nuts.

title: argentine potato salad
directions: Peel, wash and dice potatoes and carrots.
Boil until tender. Drain.
Add peas, chopped boiled eggs, oil and salt.
Mix gently. Add a few drops of milk to mayonnaise and pour over salad.
Mix.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Combine sausage in a medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until brown, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese. Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over sausage. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 5 minutes, cut into squares and serve immediately.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in double boiler.
Add flour, stirring continuously.
Stir in milk, a little at a time.
Add salt, pepper, dry mustard and garlic salt.
Stir until blended.
Add cheese to sauce and stir until melted.
Mix with 1 pound cooked elbow macaroni and bake in moderate oven (350°) until it bubbles and is lightly browned along the edges.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Crust:
Combine graham cracker crumbs and melted butter. Press mixture evenly on bottom and 1 inch up on sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Add potatoes and onions and just enough water to cover.
Cook in a covered pot for 15 minutes.
Drain; and keep 1 1/2 cups of potato water.
Mash potatoes.
Add butter, milk potato water, salt and parsley.
If a thinner soup is desired, add more water.

title: party sausage balls
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Then make round balls, size of walnuts.
Place on cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Then turn them over and bake 10 minutes more.
Drain on paper towels.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients together well and pour into two greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Cream oil, sugar, salt and eggs well.
Add yeast to water. When it has cooled, add to mixture.
Add flour and mix well.
Put in refrigerator.

title: batter-fried shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, leaving tails on; devein.
Split shrimp partway through, butterfly fashion.
Combine flour, water, egg, sugar and salt to make a batter.
Dip shrimp into batter and fry in deep, hot (375°) Planter's peanut oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook rice on package instructions. Add margarine. Stir until melted. Add corn, soup and cheese. Top with additional cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 or more. Freezes well.

title: easy dorito bake
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. (May season with chili powder and chopped onions.)

title: carrot casserole
directions: Parboil sliced carrot rounds.
Mix together ingredients with carrots.
Put in casserole.
Top with 14 saltine crackers (1/2 cup crushed), 1 tablespoon butter and 2 tablespoons parsley.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Add 1/2 cup shredded American cheese until melted.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add milk and egg yolks.
Beat well.
Cook until it thickens stirring constantly.
Add coconut and bring back to a boil.
Pour into 9 inch baked pie shell. use 3 egg whites to make meringue.
To make meringue, beat egg whites.
When they begin to stiffen add sugar-2 Tbsp. per egg white.

title: appetizer beef patties
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients into a bowl, mixing well.
Shape into bite-size patties.
Place into baking dish, bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Blend soup, cream and mustard in saucepan. Cook until heated, stirring often.
Serve patties on toothpicks with cheese sauce.

title: taco dip
directions: In bowl, combine sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning. Beat until creamy smooth.
Mix in Mozzarella cheese, Cheddar cheese, diced tomatoes and onion.
Mix them in with mixture.
Add taco sauce and heat in microwave.
Great with taco chips.

title: picnic rolls
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients; mix until cheese melts.
Spoon on buns.
This is enough for 8 hamburger buns.
Wrap in foil and put in oven until warm.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Spread chicken over bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chopped onion over chicken.
Cover chicken with cheese slices or grated cheese.
Cover with half bag of Doritos.
Mix mushroom soup, cream of celery soup and Ro-Tel.
Pour over chips.
Put rest of Doritos on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: holiday oyster stew
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and egg. Blend in the remaining ingredients.

Cover and chill about 1 hour. Heat oven to 375°. Shape the dough into 1 inch balls and place them 3 inches apart on a lightly greased baking sheet. Dip a fork in flour or sugar and press on each ball in a crisscross pattern to flatten to about 2 inches.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set but not hard.
Immediately remove the cookies from the baking sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: peppermint fudge cake
directions: Bake chocolate cake mix in thin pan to make cake about 1-inch thick when baked.
Cool and cut into squares.
Slice ice cream into squares the size of your cake.
Layer with cake on bottom and top with ice cream.
Heat hot fudge topping and pour over cake and ice cream.
Can be frozen ahead of time for parties or meals.

title: butter rolls
directions: Make dough, using flour, baking powder, baking soda, shortening and buttermilk.
Divide dough in two parts and roll out like pie crust.
Melt margarine and spread on dough (with pastry brush, if available), then sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Roll up as for cinnamon roll.
Cut in 1-inch lengths.

title: mezetti
directions: Brown ground beef, green pepper, chopped onion, chili powder and garlic salt. Drain off grease. Sprinkle noodles on top and add 1 cup water. Mix soups and mushrooms, if desired, and pour over mixture. Simmer for 25 minutes. Add cheese and heat for 5 more minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: taco dip
directions: Place in pie pan starting with 1st Layer.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: hospitality pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Bake in a preheated, oiled waffle iron.
Serve hot with desired topping.
Yield:
3 (8-inch) waffles.

title: green tomato pie
directions: Mix all together in a pan.
Cook on top of stove until comes to a good boil.
Put in unbaked double crust.
Bake at 400° until golden brown.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix together.
Add three heaping spoonfuls per cup of boiling water.

title: grandma's gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add gumdrops and coconut; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° around 12 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes and bake in tube pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before removing.

title: yummy squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread in a well buttered 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly brown. Cool about 10 minutes.
Cut in squares and remove from pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into strips.
In large skillet, brown meat.
Stir in soup mix and 2 cups water.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in pepper strips; cook.
Simmer until meat and pepper are tender. Blend cornstarch with 1/2 cup of water.
Stir in skillet until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: meat loaf
directions: Microwave onion and green pepper in small amount of oil or butter for 2 minutes on High.
Dissolve bouillon in this.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes, pour remaining 1/3 of sauce across top.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Split chiles and cover bottom and sides of casserole.
Spread cheese over chiles.
Stir eggs into milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
At this point, mixture may be refrigerated overnight. When ready to bake, top with green onions. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, or until it bubbles and puffs up.

title: barbecued "crock-pot" chicken
directions: Place the ingredients in a 3 1/2-quart crock-pot and in the order listed.
Stir once.
Turn pot to low setting and cook overnight.
Remove bones from chicken and serve meat and sauce over hot rice.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle butterscotch chips on top with sugar.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry salad dessert(frozen)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Fold in 1 large container Cool Whip.
Freeze.
Needs little, if any, thawing before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and Crisco.
Set aside.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, salt, milk, lemon flavoring and eggs, one at a time.
In a large bowl, combine creamed and flour mixtures.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Do not open oven door while cooking.

title: nana's creamy rice pudding
directions: In a heavy saucepan, cook milk and salt; stir in rice.
When mixture reaches the boiling point, lower heat and simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and continue to simmer mixture until rice is done (5 to 10 minutes).
In a mixing bowl, combine evaporated milk, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
When rice is done, stir some of the rice mixture into the egg mixture. Return this mixture to the one in the saucepan and cook slowly until it thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Don't let it curdle!

title: fancy sugared nuts
directions: Place nuts on a shallow pan.
Heat in a 375° oven for 15 minutes.
Stir often.
Cook sugar, water, salt and cinnamon to soft ball stage (236° without stirring).
Remove from heat and add vanilla and nuts.
Stir slowly until nuts are covered and become creamy.
Turn out onto a buttered platter.
Separate nut halves as they cool.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Stir at slow boil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well.
Chill.
Form into balls and put a toothpick through each.
Refrigerate for 3 hours. Melt chocolate chip morsels (must be real chocolate) and paraffin. Dip balls and refrigerate.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Combine with mixer the softened cream cheese, vanilla and brown sugar.
Refrigerate.
Just before serving, stir in peanuts. Serve with apple slices.

title: stew
directions: Mix raw.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: chocolate-chocolate cake
directions: Mix together flour and sugar in a large bowl. Set aside.
Put margarine, cocoa and water in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Pour cocoa mixture over flour and sugar. Mix until well blended. Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, cinnamon and vanilla. Mix well. Batter will be thin.
Pour batter into greased and floured 11 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
As soon as cake is removed from the oven, spread icing on top.

title: pat's pizza macaroni
directions: Brown onions and hamburg, add tomato sauce and cook 15 minutes until thickened.
Cook macaroni as directed, drain and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat milk and egg together and pour over macaroni, then spread hamburg mixture over all.
Top with slices of cheese then bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: cook-and-cut fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Add flavoring.
Add the cherries and pineapple and pecans.
Bake in greased tube cake pan.
Start to bake in a cold oven at 275° for 2 to 3 hours.
(I place a pan of water on the rack under the cake while it bakes to keep it moist.)

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Place cucumber and onion in bowl.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese together.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: raspberry yogurt
directions: With vanilla, no sugar.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Melt butter or margarine and saute onions
until clear. Add soup, mushrooms (with liquid) and cheese until
it
melts. Add cooked broccoli.
Serve hot with your favorite cracker.

title: bacon lattice steaks
directions: Cut bacon in thin strips.
Insert bacon into slashes to form lattice.
Press with palm of hand.
Season steaks with pepper. Brush all over with olive oil.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Put some olive oil and butter in a skillet.
Add fresh garlic, basil, parsley, oregano and a little salt and pepper.
Use whole baby clams, 1 small can per serving.
Add the juice to the pan and add the clams at the last minute,
just to heat them.
If you let them cook, they become tough.
Pour over linguini or other long pasta.

title: angel delight candy
directions: Boil 6 minutes; do not stir.

title: fancy franks
directions: Cut franks into thirds.
Cut bacon strips into thirds.
Wrap bacon around frank piece; secure with toothpick.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar on top until completely coated.
Bake 1 hour, uncovered, at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great for parties!

title: wild rice and oyster casserole
directions: Combine rice and butter in bowl; mix well.
Place half the rice in a large baking dish.
Arrange oysters over top; season with salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Cover with remaining rice.
Heat soup and cream in saucepan; season with onion powder, thyme and curry powder dissolved in 1/4 cup hot water.
Mix well. Pour over rice; bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices; mix.
Blend in eggs, butter and evaporated milk.
Pour into pie shell with high crimped edges.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and onions.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Add hot pepper, sugar, salt and vinegar.
Let come to a boil.
Pack in jars and seal.

title: lo-fat lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix egg substitute, fructose, nonfat yogurt, vanilla, lemon juice and rind together.
Fold in flours; put mixture in a loaf or Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Crust:
Mix flour, butter and powdered sugar until creamy and spread over pizza pan (keep hands floured).
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chili mac
directions: In a skillet brown onion and ground beef in the oil.
Drain off the fat.
Stir in salt and chili powder.
Stir in tomato bits, beans and macaroni (cooked beforehand).
Put into casserole dish and put into a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: old world apple pie
directions: Set aside apples.
Combine other 6 ingredients and mix well. Add apples.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle topping over pie and bake 20 more minutes.

title: graham toffees
directions: Microwave 1 tablespoon butter or margarine in 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Heat on High for 1 minute.
Spread the butter around the bottom and sides.
Line the bottom of dish with graham cracker squares.
In a microwave bowl, combine 1/2 cup butter and sugar on High for 1 minute.
Beat with wire whisk until smooth.
Microwave for 2 minutes.
Pour over crackers.
Spread carefully with straight-edged spatula with nuts.
Rotate 1/4 of turn every 30 seconds; boil at least 1 minute.
Cool 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with chocolate (spread); let cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: *If you use sweetened applesauce, use 1 1/2 cups sugar.

title: chow mein cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Mix noodles and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and store in a cool dry place.

title: diabetic coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: onion casserole
directions: Cook onions in salt water until fork-tender with 1/4 stick oleo.
Add soup.
Sprinkle top with Chinese noodles and almonds. Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: zucchini omelet
directions: Saute sliced zucchini in drippings.
When tender mix in beaten eggs.
When eggs are set (done) turn off heat and sprinkle seasonings and cheese over zucchini, eggs and place lid over until cheese melts.
Enjoy.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs until thickened and pale. Stir in oil. Sift together flour, soda baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in egg mixture. Fold in carrots and nuts. Spoon batter into greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 35 - 40 minutes. Cool.

title: cranberry-orange relish
directions: Cut all larger fruit into small pieces.
Put cranberries, oranges, lemon (rinds too) and apple through food processor.
Add sugar.
Chill.
Just great!

title: japanese fruit pies
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: coq au vin
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in plastic or paper bag.
Shake chicken in bag, 2 or 3 pieces at a time, until coated.
Brown chicken in oil.
Remove to a warm platter.
Cook and stir mushrooms and onion until onion is tender.
Place chicken in a Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients, except parsley.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until thick and chicken is tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle parsley over.

title: pot roast(lo-fat)
directions: Spray cold Dutch oven.
Preheat over medium-high heat and then brown the meat on all sides.
Add tomatoes, chopped onion, tomato juice, bay leaves, garlic, bouillon cubes, basil and pepper. Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, covered.

title: hot slaw
directions: Cut the cabbage; add 1 cup water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients but the canned milk; simmer until thickened. Remove from stove and add canned milk.

title: yugoslav christmas cookies
directions: Work butter until creamy.
Stir in 1/2 cup sugar gradually. Beat until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and salt.
Stir in flour.
Mix well.
Pat into a thin layer in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Beat jelly slightly with a fork and spread on dough.
Whip egg whites until stiff.
Gradually add remaining sugar, continuing to whip until mixture stands in peaks.
Fold in ground nuts and flavoring.
Swirl over jelly.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350° until brown.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter well.
Add vanilla.
Gradually stir flour into creamed ingredients.
Work nuts into dough. Chill well.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in hot oven (about 400°) for 8 to 10 minutes, until set but not brown.
Remove from oven and roll quickly in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll again.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil, drain, peel and cool sweet potatoes.
Mash thoroughly. Mix together sweet potatoes, butter, sugar, eggs and milk.
Blend well. Add spices and flavorings and mix well.
Divide evenly among 3 pie shells. Bake at 350° for 1 hour until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chris' potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cream until fluffy.
Drop on ungreased baking sheet by teaspoon.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken by covering with water in saucepan.
Bring to boil, lower heat and cook 45 minutes or until done.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Butter 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: ryan's spaghetti
directions: Saute onions and celery in 1 tablespoon butter.
Add ground beef and saute.
Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in bananas.
Line bottom of bread pan with waxed paper.
Do not grease or flour sides.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Insert knife in center of loaf to check when done.
Knife should come out "clean."
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: pineapple chicken salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and oranges; refrigerate overnight.
Mix all ingredients, but fruit.
Cover; refrigerate for several hours. Just before serving, add drained fruit.
Serve on lettuce. Serves 6 to 10.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix Bisquick, eggs and oil; add zucchini and mix well.
Put in 9 x 10-inch buttered pie dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown in oven at 350°.
Eat hot or cold.
Best when eaten warm.

title: cream cheese - salsa dip
directions: Mix cheese, salsa and salt and blend together.
Spread on plate and microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve with tacos.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add Hershey's syrup. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.
Mix the powdered sugar, butter and creme de menthe.
Spread over brownie layer.
Melt chocolate chips and butter; spread over frosting.

title: tender roast beef
directions: Place meat in crock-pot.
Mix onion soup and beef consomme. Pour over meat and add bay leaf, peppercorns and mushrooms.
Cover and cook 10 to 12 hours on low or 5 to 6 hours or high.
Cook day ahead, cool and refrigerate overnight.
Cuts easily when cold. Freezes well also.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put oats and coconut in a large bowl.
Mix well.
In a saucepan combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa.
Boil 2 minutes or until forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from stove and add vanilla.
Pour in first mixture in bowl and mix well.
With a spoon, drop cookies on tinfoil and cool.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients and heat until almost boiling.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add water to syrup to make 1 1/4 cups.
Heat to a boil.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, salt and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Fold whipped cream into Jell-O mixture.
Mold in 12 x 7-inch dish.
Better if made the day before you serve it. Serves 8 to 10.

title: meat loaf teriyaki style
directions: Drain pineapple. Save juice, reserving 1/4 cup juice and 2 teaspoons of pineapple.
Set aside.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Trim off dark green and pink parts of watermelon rind.
Cut 1-inch or any shape desired.
Soak in lime water (1 tablespoon slacked lime to each quart of water) for 4 hours.
Drain and rinse. Cover with cold water and cook until tender but not soft. Drain. Combine sugar, vinegar, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to boiling point.
Pour over rind and let stand overnight.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in oil in large saucepan. Stir in ham, crushed tomatoes, water, seasonings and rice.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; boil gently covered for 20 to 25 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add shrimp.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: moist chocolate fudge and cherry cake
directions: In mixing bowl, add cake mix. Make hole in center. Add eggs and beat, then add cherry pie filling. Mix. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan in a 375° oven. Bake for 24 to 33 minutes.

title: frosty peach pie supreme
directions: Place chopped peaches in a bowl. Stir in yogurt. Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into the crust. Cover and freeze for 4 hours or until firm. Refrigerate for 45 minutes before slicing. Top with remaining peaches. Yields 8 servings.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 3 minutes. Gradually beat in sugar. Stir pumpkin and lemon juice. Fold dry ingredients into the pumpkin. Spread into greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Top with pecans. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel that has been sprinkled with powdered sugar. Starting at narrow end, roll cake and towel together. Cool. Unroll and spread filling over cooled cake; roll. Chill, slice and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Roll fine the graham crackers and mix well with margarine and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Line 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 12-inch baking pan with the crumbs, saving 1/4 cup for topping.
This can be baked for a few minutes in about a 325° oven (a little more tasty and hold together better).
At the same time, toast the 1/4 cup of crumbs in another pie pan.
Let cool.

title: garden club meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, crumbs, onions, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Mix well and add dry ingredients.
If dough is too sticky to roll, add a little more flour.
Roll on floured surface.
Cut in shapes.
Bake on ungreased sheet at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy bread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, stirring well.
Brush on rolls. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and poppy seed.

title: 10-minute peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass mixing bowl. Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave 2 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 and 4 minutes, until syrup and peanuts are lightly browned.
Stir in butter, vanilla and soda until light and foamy.
Spread to 1/4-inch thickness on well buttered sheet of tinfoil.
Let cool; break into small pieces.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together using a fork or pastry blender. Press into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. While baking, prepare filling.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Batter chicken with seasoned flour and brown in hot oil. Remove chicken and saute celery and onion.
Drain excess fat. Add soup, water and pimientos.
Blend well. Add chicken, cover and bake at 325° about 1 hour. Turn pieces of chicken once while cooking. Serve over rice.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and lightly flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together butter, oil and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in flavorings.
Combine dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Stir in zucchini.

title: beef stew
directions: Season
meat with salt; roll in flour.
Brown slowly in oil in
heavy
saucepan.
Add
hot
water,
tomato
sauce and seasonings.
Cover tightly.
Simmer gently, about 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes, carrots and onion; cook 45 minutes longer.
Add peas last 10 to 15 minutes cooking time.

title: new orleans zucchini(light recipe)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a skillet or large saucepan.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until crisp-tender. Makes four 2/3-cup servings.
Contains 48 calories.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar together.
Blend buttermilk and soda.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients until consistency of rice grains.
Gradually add milk to shortening mixture.
Turn onto lightly floured board.
Knead gently 5 to 6 times.
Roll out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 12 to 16 biscuits.

title: party tuna ball
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients.
Stir in tuna and celery.
Mix well and chill for several hours.
Roll tuna ball in nuts and parsley on waxed paper.
Serve with crackers.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Let cream come to room temperature.
Cook fettuccine.
Drain well.
Return fettuccine to the hot saucepan.
Add cream, Parmesan cheese and margarine or butter.
Toss gently until fettuccine is well coated.
Transfer to a warm serving dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and nutmeg.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ranch bread
directions: Cut bread into slices and lay face up on a cookie sheet.
Melt butter and mix in dressing packet.
Brush bread with butter mixture.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until toasted.

title: death by chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Coarsely chop 1 pkg. of the chocolate, set aside.
Microwave remaining 8 squares in large bowl on high 1- 2 minutes.
Stir until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Stir is sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder. Stir in reserved chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 12-13 minutes or until cookies are puffed and feel set to the touch.
Cool on cookie sheet 1 minute and transfer to wire rack.

title: coffee cake
directions: Dip biscuits in melted butter, then roll in brown sugar/nut mixture.
Put in Bundt tube pan, arranged alternately as bricks, 5 on bottom row, 5 on second row.
Continue with second can.
Makes 4 layers.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Freeze from this mixture 1 tray of cubes to serve in punch.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: chicken green chile stew
directions: Boil potatoes as for potato soup, drain and set aside.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill pie plate with sliced apples.
Mix together sugar and flour.
Cut in 6 tablespoons butter.
Spread evenly over apples.

title: sweet potato-cranberry casserole
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Arrange in a shallow baking dish.
Combine orange rind, orange juice, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over potatoes and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes, basting after 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; cover with cranberries and bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Brown onion and butter; add soup, milk, salt and pepper. Simmer over low heat for about 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles; drain well and place in casserole dish.
Pour all ingredients over noodles. Add bread crumbs and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Wash vegetables; drain and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Stir in Ranch dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: chicken, vegetable and dumplings
directions: Season the chicken and fry in a large electric skillet.
When brown, add the water and onion and simmer for 30 minutes, covered. Then add the soup, water and vegetables; simmer 10 minutes.
Mix the Bisquick and milk. Drop 12 to 14 dumplings into the stew. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes, then flip the dumplings and cook 20 minutes, covered.
Total cooking time:
1 1/2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and Italian dressing; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: tuna salad
directions: Add nuts and noodles just before serving.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Add sugar and Karo syrup.
Stir until dissolved.
Cook to 240° on candy thermometer.
Add raw peanuts. Cook to 310°, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add butter and vanilla, then soda.
Stir quickly.
Mixture will foam. Spread on well buttered or foil-lined cookie sheet (10 x 14-inches); cool.
Remove foil.
Break into pieces.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: In butter, saute cashews, sesame seeds and almonds. Cook the cooking oil (vegetable), sesame oil,
rice vinegar, sugar, Accent, salt and pepper together to almost boil, then cool. Toss all ingredients just prior to serving with Ramen noodles (do not use seasoning packets).

title: holiday bread
directions: Grease and flour four 1 pound coffee cans.
Heat oven to 350°. Mix all dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin, eggs, oil and water.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.
Fill coffee cans half full.
Bake 1 hour.

title: hotsy's cookies
directions: Crush graham crackers in blender until fine.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in 11 x 7-inch greased pan.
Bake. Cool and cut into squares.
So easy and good!

title: the big easy breakfast
directions: Cook sausage in large skillet over medium heat until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Add oil.
Heat over medium-high heat.
Add potatoes and peppers.
Cover.
Cook 8 to 10 minutes or to desired crispness.
Stir in sausage.
Remove from heat.
Top with Velveeta cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and thick.
Blend in lime juice then milk, stirring until mixture thickens.
If desired add a few drops green food coloring.
Pour mixture into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff. Gradually beat in sugar beating until glassy peaks form.
Spread egg whites over surface of pie to edge of crust.
Bake in 350° oven until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Chill before serving.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots and cool; add onions and green pepper.
Mix other ingredients together; pour over carrots.
Cover and marinate for 12 hours or more.
Drain and serve.
