Will keep 2 to 3 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In bowl combine peanut butter, milk powder and honey.
Stir in marshmallows and raisins.
Sprinkle with water.
Mix well.
Press into a small loaf pan.
Cover and chill 1 hour or until firm. Remove from pan and cut into squares.
Store in covered container.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix brown sugar, butter, and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown (approximately 10-12 minutes).
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Cool slightly. May add frosting.

title: potato candy
directions: Combine vanilla and potatoes.
Slowly add sugar until stiff dough.
Take small portions and roll out thin on wax paper. Spread desired amount of peanut butter; roll in jelly roll fashion.
Cool 1 hour.
Cut into small bite-size pieces.

title: low fat blueberry dessert
directions: Layer graham crackers in bottom of 13 x 9 dish. Mix pudding, milk and water. Mix until thick. Add Cool Whip. Layer crackers and pudding mix 3 times. Top with blueberry pie filling. Store in refrigerator.

title: coconut angel food cake
directions: Have egg whites at room temperature.
Measure sifted flour; add 1/2 cup sugar, sifted together four times.
Combine egg whites, salt, cream of tartar and flavoring in large bowl.
Beat until moist soft peaks form.
Add rest of sugar in four additions, folding until blended each time.
Sift in flour mixture in four additions, folding in with large spoon.
(Keep turning bowl around.)
When folding in flour and sugar, fold in 1 cup of Angel Flake coconut.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes in ungreased 10-inch tube pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar, marshmallows and apples.
Let set. When set, add Jell-O and sugar; mix.
Add nuts and whipped cream for topping.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour with 1/2 cup of the sugar 4 times.

Beat egg whites with cream of tartar, salt and flavorings in large bowl at high speed with electric mixer until stiff peaks form. Gradually add the remaining 1 1/3 cups sugar, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in flour mixture. Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched with finger.
Invert pan and allow cake to cool completely in pan before removing from pan. Serve with strawberries, if desired.
Makes one 10-inch tube cake.

title: easy bake beans
directions: Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Top with bacon or put bacon on top and bake in microwave oven for 10 to 13 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Seal in hot sterilized jars.
Makes 4 pints.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine chicken soup, onion, celery, rice, almonds and Miracle Whip.
Mix well.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, 3-quart.
In pan where butter was melted, combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until casserole bubbles and crumbs are brown.
Makes about 10 servings.
Can make ahead and freeze.
You can also use turkey.

title: baked mushroom appetizer
directions: Clean and remove stems from mushrooms.
Set caps aside. Finely chop stems.
Combine stems, beef, catsup, 3 tablespoons bread crumbs, onion, seasoned salt and garlic salt.
Mound into mushroom caps. Dip filled side of caps into remaining 3 tablespoons bread crumbs to coat mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika. Place filled side up in a shallow pan.
Add warm water to cover bottom of pan, about 1/2-inch deep.
Bake in a 350° oven about 35 minutes or until light brown on top. Serve warm.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium skillet, saute onion in butter until translucent.
Stir in chicken, 1 cup taco sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer, uncovered, over low heat 15 minutes.

title: no mess pie crust
directions: Mix in pie pan and smooth out to form crust.
No rolling

title: orange julius
directions: Blend all together in blender for 30 seconds.
Serves 5 or 6.

title: millionaires
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat.
Add pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered waxed paper; chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate morsels in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Dip candy into chocolate and return to waxed paper.
Chill.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours before serving.
Best served with a round or rye bread hollowed out in the center of the bread and spoon dip into the bread bowl. Use the bread that has been cut out for dipping.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Combine ingredients; mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until light brown and bubbles.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cut up onions and squash.
Boil in water for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and coarsely mash together.
Add milk, egg, salt, pepper, basil, marjoram and cheese.
Put in greased casserole.
Top with pats of butter and cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix above ingredients together and put into a dish.
Add marchino cherries if desired.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together and spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 to minutes.

title: mexican taco dip
directions: Blend all ingreds. with mixer.
Smooth on a baking pan.
Top with shredded lettuce, diced tomato and diced onion and shredded cheddar cheese. Serve with Tortilla chips.

title: simple dessert
directions: Blend all together.
Refrigerate.
Put into a glass bowl and spoon out.

title: hot chicken salad i
directions: Mix all ingredients together except for cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture into large casserole sprayed with Pam.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbling hot, approximately 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine the first 4 ingredients in a mixing bowl.
In another bowl, combine the egg whites, buttermilk and oil.
Combine dry and wet ingredients together and stir together vigorously until smoothly blended.
Stir in the jalapenos, cheese and corn.
Pour in an oiled 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, or until the top just begins to turn golden and a knife inserted into the center tests done.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Bring oil and water to a boil and pour over flour. Stir until it holds together. Cool. Pat out in pie pan.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large pot, pour milk, butter, salt and flour.
Stir.
Add pepper and warm.
Add diced potatoes, cut up broccoli, chopped onion and flour.
Add water.
Let cook on medium temperature until vegetables are tender.
Add cheese.
Simmer.

title: cranberry fruit
directions: Mash up cranberry sauce until fairly smooth.
Add other fruit with juices.
This is simple, but good!

title: stuffed clams
directions: Saute bacon, onion and garlic until bacon is well cooked; add chopped clams until they are cooked through.
Add bread stuffing, then add the wine to add moisture and lemons.
Put into ramekins on baking sheet; cook until crispy.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top, if desired.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham, pork, beaten eggs, milk and bread crumbs.
Mix together brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and water.
Pour over ham loaf.
Baste loaf several times while baking.

title: hall's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter and mix together.
Fold in 1/2 Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crust. Add remaining Cool Whip on top.
Refrigerate.

title: bertha's yellow cake
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, beat, then repeat.
Mash bananas to measure 1 cup.
Add flour mixture and bananas alternately.
Mix at low speed to blend.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Push batter into corners.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: two corn casserole
directions: Mix together onion, mango and butter and brown in skillet, then add remaining ingredients. Mix well. Spray an oblong baking dish with Pam. Pour mixture into baking dish. Spread 4 ounces or more (whatever desired) to cover top of mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese bake appetizer
directions: Combine first three ingredients and stir in cheese and onion. Spoon into a 1-quart dish and bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until puffed and golden.

title: brittney's special chicken soup
directions: Place chicken and water in a large kettle or Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Add onion, celery, bouillon, parsley sprigs, garlic and salt, if desired.
Cover and simmer until the chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Allow to cool. Strain and reserve broth; discard vegetables.
Add carrots to broth and simmer until tender, about 15 minutes.
Debone chicken; cut into cubes.
Add chicken and chopped parsley to broth; heat through.
Ladle into bowls; add rice to each bowl.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt
margarine.
Mix
sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs.
Add milk and vanilla. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: I use a food processor on carrots and onion. Let marinate in refrigerator overnight. If there is leftover marinade after vegetables are used, you can marinate meat in it or use on any other salad. This dressing is great because it doesn't separate!

title: baked turnips with peanuts
directions: Arrange turnips, onion and peanuts in well-greased baking dish. Dot with butter; add salt and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in a moderate oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley. Makes 6 servings.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Beat in whole egg and egg yolk.

Sift flour and soda with 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg. Mix into butter. Fold in nuts and raisins. Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto buttered cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, one at a time, then mashed bananas.
Combine dry ingredients.
Sift into mixture alternately with sour milk.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in loaf pan, greased.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool and wrap in foil and keep in refrigerator.

title: pork chop delight
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Brush with mustard.
Mix egg and water and dip chops.
Mix soup and milk together for sauce.
Pour over chops and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: mandarin orange mold
directions: Drain 1 can of oranges and reserve liquid.
Add enough water to syrup from oranges to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour in saucepan; boil.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add sherbet; stir until melted.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill until firm.
Garnish with watercress and oranges, drained and whole strawberries.

title: pancake pudding cake(country kettle opryland usa)
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and set aside. Combine eggs, sugars, cinnamon and vanilla; blend together. Add oatmeal mixture, blending well. Add pancake mix last and blend well. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: texas flank steak
directions: Place flank steak in a shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over steak.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours, turning steak often.
Drain steak, reserving marinade. Grill steak over hot coals 10 to 12 minutes on each side or to desired degree of doneness, basting occasionally, with reserved marinade.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: gourmet crab casserole
directions: In bowl, mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Add crabmeat and stir until combined.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Grease and flour tube or Bundt cake pan. Combine ingredients, adding eggs one at a time. Pour in 1/2 the batter. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle on top of batter. Pour in rest of batter. Bake at 350° for 65 minutes; cool.

title: hummers
directions: Put Kahlua, rum and creme de cacao in blender.
Fill with ice cream.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Blend and serve. Serves 6.
Very rich.
Gets name from everyone saying umm!

title: fish stew
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble.
Discard 1/2 of grease, then fry cut onions in remaining grease until slightly brown.
Add bacon, fish pieces and the juices and spices.
Heat to a slow boil in an uncovered pot for 45 to 60 minutes to cook fish and thicken sauce.
This should fill up a 4-quart pot.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut-beer shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tail on. Mix spices in covered bowl. Add shrimp and shake until coated. Combine flour, beer, egg and baking powder. Spread coconut on a baking sheet. Dip shrimp in batter, then lay in the coconut. Turn to coat well. Deep-fry until golden.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar and water in the top of a double boiler over boiling water.
Beat at high speed until frosting holds its shape, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Beat in vanilla.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: chocolate brownie pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Heat chocolate and margarine over low heat until melted; cool.
Beat chocolate mixture, eggs, sugar and corn syrup with a hand beater.
Pour into pastry-lined pie plate.
Bake just until set, 40 to 50 minutes. Serve with sweetened whipped cream, if desired.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Roll cookies into crumbs.
Cut in 1/2 stick butter and press in pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 4 minutes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish. Top with more cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Blend shortening and sugar.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture.
Mash bananas until smooth; add lemon juice and blend with mixture.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt; quickly add to the banana mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: egg salad
directions: Lightly toss all ingredients except bacon.
Chill.
Add bacon before serving.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or bread sticks.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix banana, pineapple and lemon juice; add other ingredients and mix together.
Spoon into paper baking cups and freeze.

title: pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat until well mixed. Pour into ungreased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Allow cake to cool in pan.
Remove from pan to serving plate.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell. Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli enough to break up.
Place broccoli and water chestnuts in a 2-quart casserole and mix.
Cover with soup.
Mix bread crumbs, cheese and melted butter and sprinkle on top of soup.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in a large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Combine all other ingredients in a 2-1/2 quart casserole dish and add ground beef mixture.
Mix well.
Place bacon slices on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Sift sugar, cocoa and salt.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Place butter on top. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Beat with wooden spoon.
Spread into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch cooking dish. Freeze about 1 hour.

title: busy day beef stew
directions: Put in large covered casserole.
Cook at 250° for 5 hours, 1/2 recipe 4 hours.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Crush graham crackers; add to mixture.
Add coconut; mix well.
Shape into balls.
Melt 1 package of chocolate morsels and 1 stick paraffin; dip balls.

title: frosty fruit loaf
directions: Drain fruit cocktail, reserving 1/2 cup juice/syrup.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over juice.
Stir in strawberries and corn syrup.
Chill until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from spoon.
Fold in fruit cocktail and yogurt.
Spoon into 9-inch loaf pan.
Cover.
Freeze until firm.
Serves 8.

title: fried pie dough
directions: Mix together and divide into balls.
Press out on wax paper. Add fruit and crimp edges.
Fry in deep fryer.

title: turtle pretzels
directions: Wrap all but the top portion of a pretzel rod with a piece of caramel.
Melt chocolate.
Dip pretzel in melted chocolate and pecan mixture.
Layer pretzels on waxed paper until set.

title: party mix
directions: Divide cereals, nuts, chip and pretzels into 4 big roaster pans.

title: simple apple pie
directions: Combine flour, cream cheese and margarine in a bowl, working into a smooth pastry.
Put pastry into refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Peel and slice apples.
Roll out pastry on a well floured surface.
Place pastry into a baking pan.
Neatly arrange apples on top of pastry.
Sprinkle apples with sugar, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Cut butter into bits and put evenly on top of apples and spices. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked haddock fillet
directions: Cover fish in olive oil.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Salt and pepper, if desired.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tossed salad.

title: everything deluxe(sandwiches)
directions: Spread peanut butter on one pancake.
Spread cream cheese on other pancake.
Spread on applesauce.
Place shaved carrots on applesauce.
Put pancakes together like sandwich.
Refrigerate until well chilled.

title: good dessert
directions: Mix in large bowl. Chill and serve.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and broccoli.
Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until rice is done.

title: danny's favorite potato soup
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, celery, pepper, salt and broth in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 20 minutes.*
Cook bacon in skillet until crisp.
Remove bacon, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside. Add flour to drippings in skillet.
Stir until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Gradually stir milk mixture and bacon into potato mixture.
Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.

title: veal chops with sage
directions: Sprinkle chops with pepper.
Melt 3 tablespoons of the butter in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat; add chops.
Reduce heat to medium and cook on one side until browned (8 to 10 minutes).
Turn chops, sprinkle sage into butter and cook until chops are browned and meat near bone is no longer pink when slashed (about 10 minutes).
Arrange chops on a platter; keep warm.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Press biscuits out and cut in halves.
Place apple piece in each half of biscuit and roll up.
Melt margarine and mix with sugar and water.
Pour over dumplings.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti according to package directions and drain.
Remove casings from sausage links. Brown sausage in a large skillet, stirring occasionally. Saute onion in sausage drippings. Drain off excess fat.

Combine ziti, sausage/onion mixture, spaghetti sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and Ricotta cheese. Spoon mixture into 3 1/2-quart casserole. Top with Parmesan and remaining Mozzarella cheese. Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender, except pecans.
Blend well and set aside.
Lightly butter the inside of uncooked pie shell and cover with pecans.
Pour liquid into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350° and cook for an additional 30 minutes.
If pie is still a little wiggly, reduce heat to 325° and bake for 5 more minutes.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour into pan.
Tilt to cover all
of the bottom.
Add all other ingredients and stir well with a fork until blended (2 minutes).
Spread evenly over the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, when tester comes out clean.

title: delicious potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Cook celery, pepper, onions in oleo until tender.
Add milk, soup and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Pour over potatoes in casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 375° until bubbly.

title: salsa dip
directions: Blend in blender to mix.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken livers and mushrooms
directions: Saute liver slowly in oil. Add red wine and mushrooms.
Heat and serve over rice. Serves 4.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, add bread crumbs, milk, oil, sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and raisins.
Pour into 8-inch square baking dish and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.
Top with lemon or rum sauce.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Mix well until smooth with dough hook and then put in jelly roll pan.
Cool and enjoy!

title: hello polly cake
directions: Line a 7 x 11-inch pan with graham crackers, pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour sweetened condensed milk.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: potato supreme
directions: Peel, cube, cook and drain potatoes.
Mix soup, 1/2 of cheese, sour cream, salt and pepper in bowl; add potatoes.
Grease baking dish. Place potatoes in dish; top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon and pasta
directions: Coat salmon with olive oil, slices of lemon and bay leaf. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Pout under broiler the last 5 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti, seasoned with oil, basil, Feta cheese, pepper and parsley.

title: vegetable-pasta salad
directions: Break linguine into thirds and cook according to package directions, omitting salt; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain. Combine linguine and remaining ingredients, tossing well. Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Yields 16 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put cucumbers, onions and ice in a large bowl or pan; sprinkle with salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Combine water, sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed; bring to a boil.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Take cucumbers out of salt water and add to the spice mixture.
Bring to a boil (do not boil).
Pack in jars.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Pulverize all peppers with water.
Add remaining ingredients, except Certo.
Boil hard 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Certo and few drops of food coloring.
Make red by using red peppers. Seeds will show unless strained.
Serve with cream cheese and crackers.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In medium skillet, saute onion, garlic, green pepper and celery in butter about 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in tomato sauce, water, bay leaf, parsley, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add more water if needed.
Add thawed shrimp.
Bring mixture to a boil; cook, covered, over medium heat 5 minutes. Serve Shrimp Creole over fluffy white rice.
Yields 2 generous servings.

title: polish pickles
directions: Bring to a boil and let cook for 3 minutes.
Use 1 to 2 cloves of garlic and 1 sprig of dill weed in each jar.
Put cukes in each jar with garlic and dill.
Pour hot liquid into each jar.
Put lid on and cover tight.
Let stand in cool dry place about 2 weeks. After that, put in refrigerator.

title: easy trifle
directions: Prepare pudding as directed using 1/2 cup more milk than called for (will be thin).
Cut cake lengthwise into 4 slices. Spread jam on two slices then place remaining 2 slices on top to form 2 sandwiches.
Press slightly to flatten.
Cut each sandwich into small squares.
Press 1/2 of the squares into a serving dish. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sherry.
Spread with half of the pudding.
Repeat layers.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with almonds.

title: orange sherbert salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in boiling water, add sherbert.
Stir in rest of ingredients, then fold in whipped topping.
Chill.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook salt and drain broccoli according to package directions. Add corn, 1/2 of the bread crumbs, butter and eggs.
Mix.
Place in 12 x 15-inch casserole; top with cheese.
Spread remaining bread crumbs over cheese; bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil pepperoni 5 minutes to remove fat.
Prepare rotini noodles as directed.
Brown Italian sausage.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle cheese over top and simmer until melted.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
Stir in beans.
Grate cheese.
Heat tortillas.
Put 2 tablespoons of meat and bean mixture in center of tortillas. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add salsa or hot sauce, if desired. Fold in ends and roll up.

title: tommy's grilled pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops.
Coat both sides with meat tenderizer. Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Cook over high heat on gas grill.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Cook sausage until browned.
Drain (scramble cooked sausage). Combine all ingredients and knead thoroughly to blend.
Roll into small walnut sized balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 60 or 70 balls.

title: green onion dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, onion and beef.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Miracle whip and cheese.
Mix well.
Shape into a ball.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Equally divide this mixture into two well-greased loaf pans and bake in a preheated oven at 350° until done.
This is delicious hot out of the oven or cold.

title: oriental salad
directions: Crumble noodles into a large bowl.
Add cole slaw, onion, broccoli, and sunflower seeds and toss well.

title: onion-cucumber salad
directions: In a bowl, combine oil, vinegar, sugar, water, sour cream and salt.
Add cuke and onion.
Toss to coat.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add 3 ripe bananas that have been mashed with the flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: walnut macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, walnuts, flour, cinnamon and salt in large bowl. Mix in egg whites and lemon peel. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Dip macaroon bottoms in melted chocolate. Place on waxed paper to set.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in casserole dish.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours, until rice absorbs liquid.
Stir halfway through. Bake at 350°.

title: meat loaf a la james campbell
directions: Mix vegetables and saltines with eggs.
Salt and pepper ground beef to taste.
Mix all ingredients adding a good pinch of red pepper seeds.
Make sure everything is well blended together. Form in a loaf.
Smooth top with plenty of steak sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 45 minutes or until done.
Double all ingredients for the Martin Family Reunion.

title: double delicious cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt oleo in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over oleo. Pour Eagle Brand evenly over crumbs.
Top with chips.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook the onions and carrots in 1/2 teaspoon salted water until tender. Cook squash until tender. Drain together in colander; set aside. Combine sour cream with the soup. Fold into mixture of squash, onions and carrots.

title: stir-fried potatoes and eggs
directions: Beat eggs slightly with seasoned salt, salt and wine or lemon juice.
Pour over thawed fries in a bowl.
Toss gently to mix. Heat oil in large fry pan.
Add onion and cook until golden brown. Pour in egg-potato mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until eggs are cooked and fries are heated through, about 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: slow cook chicken
directions: Mix all spices and rub thoroughly into chicken inside and out. Stuff fryer with chopped onion.
Place in plastic bag in refrigerator overnight.
Roast, uncovered, at 250° for 5 hours.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix cucumbers, onion and salt.
Refrigerate 2 hours, covered. Drain and press, but do not rinse.
Mix vinegar and sugar; mix well with cucumber mix.
Place in 1/2 pint containers and freeze.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Place ground beef, bell pepper and onion in skillet over medium heat until ground beef is done; drain.
Add corn, tomato paste and water and mix.
Boil potatoes and cream with milk and butter.

title: chocolate banana bread
directions: Combine shortening in a large bowl with sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy.
Combine milk and vinegar in small bowl.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda in small bowl.
Stir flour mixture into creamed mixture alternately with bananas.
Fold in chocolate chips, raisins and nuts.
Turn into 4 well-greased and floured 6 x 3 1/2 x 2-inch loaf pans or 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pan.
Spread to fill pans and smooth top.
Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pans to rack immediately.
Cool thoroughly before cutting or before wrapping for freezing or for gifts.
Makes 4 small or 1 large loaf.

title: tabooleh
directions: Soak cracked wheat in warm water for 1/2 hour.
Drain wheat; add remaining ingredients.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ungspankaaka(oven pancakes)
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, soft butter, sugar, salt and flour.
Pour into baking pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 425°.
(This pancake puffs up high so don't have oven rack too close on top.
When I ask my kids what they want for a different dinner, they choose this 100%.)

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla mixture.
Add flour, baking soda and salt mixture.
Stir in oats slowly.
Roll onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Chewy bake for 10 minutes.
Crispy bake for 20 minutes.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: In shallow pan, mix about 1 cup flour with salt and pepper to taste.
In separate bowl, slightly beat egg.
Add some milk and a sprinkle of flour.
Cut up chicken.
For each piece, individually coat with flour mixture, then dip into egg mixture.
Add another coating of the flour mixture.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown and well done.
It's best to use a cast-iron skillet.

title: raisin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and sift three times.
Add raisins.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar; then add egg and milk.
Add flour mixture, stirring until only smooth.
Bake in a greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch) at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: aunt sally's chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti; then mix all the ingredients together in a baking dish.
Cook in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: tarragon chicken with carrots and linguine
directions: In a large pot, cook linguine just until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, heat stock over medium heat.
Cut chicken into strips 1/2-inch wide and 3-inches long.
Add to stock.
Separate onion slices into individual rings and add to stock.
Cook for 7 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: mj's vegetables
directions: Boil carrots al dente.
At 300° or low-medium heat, place butter in skillet and melt.
Add vegetables and spices, turning 2 or 3 times until just tender (approximately 6 minutes).
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Set aside 1 cup cake mix. In mixing bowl, combine rest of cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg. Spread over bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix pumpkin, 1 cup sugar, pecans and pumpkin pie spice until blended. Add milk and 2 eggs and continue blending. Pour over the cake mix in pan.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars.
Blend candy with Eagle Brand milk and syrup. Pour into freezer and fill with whole milk.
